WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:25.856 --> 00:00:27.884
♪ ♪

3
00:00:41.973 --> 00:00:43.999
<i>(crowd clamoring)</i>

4
00:00:46.311 --> 00:00:50.076
- (boot thumping)
- CROWD: One! Two! Three!

5
00:00:50.212 --> 00:00:51.845
(laughs menacingly)

6
00:00:51.980 --> 00:00:53.516
Yeah!

7
00:00:53.652 --> 00:00:55.410
(yells)

8
00:00:55.545 --> 00:00:57.346
(yells. grunts)

9
00:00:57.481 --> 00:00:59.381
(cheering)

10
00:00:59.517 --> 00:01:01.016
Come on! Yeah!

11
00:01:03.629 --> 00:01:04.527
Come on!

12
00:01:04.663 --> 00:01:06.359
(yells)

13
00:01:06.495 --> 00:01:09.024
- (laughs)
- (crowd shouting)

14
00:01:13.433 --> 00:01:14.966
Let's do this! Come on!

15
00:01:15.102 --> 00:01:16.673
Come on!

16
00:01:16.808 --> 00:01:19.243
(yells. grunts)

17
00:01:20.406 --> 00:01:22.712
Come on! Come on!

18
00:01:22.847 --> 00:01:24.242
(chair clatters)

19
00:01:24.377 --> 00:01:26.046
(grunts) Come on.

20
00:01:26.182 --> 00:01:27.486
Let's do this. Come on.

21
00:01:27.621 --> 00:01:29.082
(crowd shouting)

22
00:01:29.218 --> 00:01:31.453
(wrestlers grunting)

23
00:01:36.222 --> 00:01:39.428
MAN: Let the backpack slip off
next time everyone stands.

24
00:01:45.771 --> 00:01:47.601
(cheering)

25
00:01:53.747 --> 00:01:54.843
Where's Jane?

26
00:01:54.978 --> 00:01:56.707
Daniel Kellner.

27
00:01:56.843 --> 00:01:59.008
Do you want to see her again
or not?

28
00:02:03.052 --> 00:02:05.784
(crowd cheering)

29
00:02:10.091 --> 00:02:11.486
Relax.

30
00:02:11.621 --> 00:02:12.954
Enjoy the match.

31
00:02:13.090 --> 00:02:15.259
Just got to make sure
it's all there.

32
00:02:15.394 --> 00:02:17.433
(crowd cheering)

33
00:02:19.632 --> 00:02:23.334
MAN 2:
7.23.48.83

34
00:02:23.469 --> 00:02:28.008
through 3.14.84A.

35
00:02:28.143 --> 00:02:29.777
11.17.55...

36
00:02:29.912 --> 00:02:34.276
I make a total of 107
IronClad drives. 128 gig each.

37
00:02:34.412 --> 00:02:37.452
- You want me to do a recount?
- Uh. when we finish. yes.

38
00:02:37.588 --> 00:02:39.890
Printed documents
approximately 200 pages.

39
00:02:40.025 --> 00:02:41.522
What's the date range?

40
00:02:41.658 --> 00:02:43.490
Uh. we can catalog that
when we get back.

41
00:02:43.625 --> 00:02:46.194
But I'm seeing
as far back as 1947

42
00:02:46.329 --> 00:02:48.398
and as recent as last year.

43
00:02:49.803 --> 00:02:51.663
(door creaks open)

44
00:02:51.799 --> 00:02:53.832
(lively crowd chatter
in distance)

45
00:02:59.009 --> 00:03:01.037
♪ ♪

46
00:03:14.686 --> 00:03:16.723
(breathing heavily)

47
00:03:28.474 --> 00:03:30.572
Well. this is all
rather disappointing.

48
00:03:33.242 --> 00:03:34.708
Where's Jane?

49
00:03:38.479 --> 00:03:40.516
(trembling breaths)

50
00:03:45.355 --> 00:03:47.083
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

51
00:03:48.592 --> 00:03:50.856
- DANIEL: Careful.
- (snips zip tie)

52
00:03:52.990 --> 00:03:54.860
- (Jane whimpering)
- Hey.

53
00:04:01.775 --> 00:04:03.541
Who turned you?

54
00:04:03.677 --> 00:04:07.745
Give me the names. all of them.
and you two can call a cab.

55
00:04:07.880 --> 00:04:09.743
It's here.

56
00:04:29.267 --> 00:04:30.929
(backpack drops to ground)

57
00:04:32.872 --> 00:04:34.229
Where is it?

58
00:04:39.403 --> 00:04:40.912
- Put your weapon on the ground!
- (others shouting)

59
00:04:41.048 --> 00:04:44.415
Do not fire! Do not fire.

60
00:04:44.550 --> 00:04:47.209
If you fire.
it could activate the device.

61
00:04:49.122 --> 00:04:51.116
Loosen your grip. Daniel.

62
00:04:52.119 --> 00:04:54.293
If you squeeze. it activates.
Soften your grip.

63
00:04:55.693 --> 00:04:57.594
Put it down.
You don't know how to use it.

64
00:04:57.730 --> 00:04:59.791
- I know how you used it.
- And it almost killed me.

65
00:04:59.927 --> 00:05:03.335
Now. place the device
on the ground.

66
00:05:03.470 --> 00:05:05.430
I should do to you
what you did to them.

67
00:05:05.566 --> 00:05:07.432
Stand down. Serena.

68
00:05:07.568 --> 00:05:10.133
(breathing heavily)

69
00:05:11.243 --> 00:05:14.275
Do not exert any pressure on it.

70
00:05:14.410 --> 00:05:16.806
Just loosen your grip.

71
00:05:16.941 --> 00:05:18.410
Loosen your grip. That's it.

72
00:05:18.546 --> 00:05:19.978
Just open your hand.

73
00:05:21.118 --> 00:05:22.149
That's it.

74
00:05:22.284 --> 00:05:23.949
Okay. Okay.

75
00:05:25.791 --> 00:05:27.990
Sweep everything into
the backpack and get in the car.

76
00:05:28.126 --> 00:05:29.592
Please. Jane.

77
00:05:32.161 --> 00:05:33.629
Get out.

78
00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:41.263
You're not running
some malware op.

79
00:05:41.399 --> 00:05:43.975
You can't hide behind a screen
in your SCIF.

80
00:05:44.111 --> 00:05:45.541
The world is on the brink.

81
00:05:45.677 --> 00:05:47.711
Do you actually believe
that dumping inventory

82
00:05:47.846 --> 00:05:50.382
will be anything more
than a dangerous distraction?

83
00:05:51.680 --> 00:05:53.308
I watched the interrogations.

84
00:05:54.421 --> 00:05:55.847
History doesn't have
a reset key.

85
00:05:55.983 --> 00:05:57.686
If you do this.
there's no undoing it.

86
00:05:59.816 --> 00:06:01.690
That's the plan.

87
00:06:02.555 --> 00:06:03.593
(engine starts)

88
00:06:05.757 --> 00:06:07.927
(tires squealing)

89
00:06:15.336 --> 00:06:17.002
Boyd.

90
00:06:21.113 --> 00:06:23.041
He sits at a desk.

91
00:06:24.282 --> 00:06:26.110
How did he beat you?

92
00:06:34.986 --> 00:06:36.594
They said you committed treason?

93
00:06:36.729 --> 00:06:38.194
It's not treason.
They're not the government.

94
00:06:38.330 --> 00:06:39.723
and they lie for a living.

95
00:06:39.859 --> 00:06:41.560
What is going on. Daniel?

96
00:06:41.696 --> 00:06:42.957
Their cars have trackers.

97
00:06:43.093 --> 00:06:44.398
We got to get rid of this.

98
00:06:44.534 --> 00:06:45.799
Please just take me home.

99
00:06:45.934 --> 00:06:47.899
They'd be waiting
at your apartment.

100
00:06:48.035 --> 00:06:50.134
Hey. hand me
the clear plastic bag.

101
00:06:53.576 --> 00:06:55.612
Okay. Steer for a second.

102
00:06:57.181 --> 00:06:59.550
Okay. Okay.

103
00:07:02.450 --> 00:07:03.749
(dialing phone)

104
00:07:03.884 --> 00:07:05.956
- Okay. okay.
- (line ringing)

105
00:07:06.091 --> 00:07:07.592
Hugo. I'm clear.

106
00:07:07.727 --> 00:07:10.218
HUGO (over phone):
Daniel. I'm so proud of you.

107
00:07:10.354 --> 00:07:12.425
They kidnapped Jane
to get to me.

108
00:07:12.560 --> 00:07:14.122
She's with me now.

109
00:07:14.257 --> 00:07:15.857
HUGO:
Is she all right?

110
00:07:15.992 --> 00:07:17.496
Not really. Hugo.

111
00:07:17.632 --> 00:07:18.931
Where do I do the drop?

112
00:07:19.066 --> 00:07:20.571
- No drop yet.
- (power tools buzzing)

113
00:07:20.706 --> 00:07:22.569
- Get secure. and then...
- DANIEL: No. no. no.

114
00:07:22.705 --> 00:07:24.574
Send the guy for the bag now.

115
00:07:24.710 --> 00:07:26.405
Somebody needs to run
with this thing.

116
00:07:26.540 --> 00:07:27.803
That's you.

117
00:07:27.939 --> 00:07:29.305
You've got the ball.

118
00:07:30.414 --> 00:07:32.179
I don't want the ball.

119
00:07:32.315 --> 00:07:34.979
No. the plan was I get it out
of the facility. and I-I did.

120
00:07:35.115 --> 00:07:36.582
HUGO: I decided
you were best qualified

121
00:07:36.718 --> 00:07:37.979
to keep the material safe.

122
00:07:38.115 --> 00:07:40.081
Are you out of your mind?

123
00:07:40.217 --> 00:07:42.626
No. I'm not a field guy. Hugo.

124
00:07:42.761 --> 00:07:44.920
I-I did the tech work.
That's all I can do.

125
00:07:45.055 --> 00:07:46.095
You just stay with me.

126
00:07:46.231 --> 00:07:47.598
We're on plan.

127
00:07:47.733 --> 00:07:50.127
Waiting now for someone else
to be activated.

128
00:07:50.263 --> 00:07:52.495
When they are.
we'll know what comes next.

129
00:07:52.631 --> 00:07:55.197
Leave Jane somewhere safe
and get secure for the night.

130
00:07:55.333 --> 00:07:57.939
Oh. no.
I-I'm not leaving her alone.

131
00:07:58.074 --> 00:08:00.602
- She'll be safer without you.
- But she wasn't.

132
00:08:00.738 --> 00:08:03.604
I'm gonna need you to drop
a marker when you get secure.

133
00:08:03.740 --> 00:08:05.947
Our friend Santiago
will find you in the morning.

134
00:08:06.082 --> 00:08:09.312
I should just dump everything
online right now.

135
00:08:11.086 --> 00:08:14.251
You cannot. under any
circumstances. do that.

136
00:08:15.854 --> 00:08:17.161
For now. we wait.

137
00:08:17.297 --> 00:08:19.058
Stay alert. Find shelter.

138
00:08:19.193 --> 00:08:21.291
Santiago will put us together
in the morning.

139
00:08:22.301 --> 00:08:23.526
Destroy your phone.

140
00:08:23.662 --> 00:08:24.961
(sighs)

141
00:08:25.096 --> 00:08:26.530
(siren wailing in distance)

142
00:08:26.665 --> 00:08:27.995
Danny.

143
00:08:28.131 --> 00:08:30.332
Satellite burner phones.

144
00:08:30.467 --> 00:08:31.934
They got their own
encrypted network.

145
00:08:32.069 --> 00:08:33.842
We only use them once.

146
00:08:36.440 --> 00:08:38.550
What exactly do you do
for a living?

147
00:08:39.949 --> 00:08:41.449
We got to get secure
for the night.

148
00:08:41.585 --> 00:08:43.380
No apartments. no motels.

149
00:08:43.516 --> 00:08:46.283
Has to be somewhere I've never
been before in my life.

150
00:08:47.625 --> 00:08:49.924
I know a place close to here.

151
00:09:01.769 --> 00:09:03.001
<i>(elevator bell chimes)</i>

152
00:09:03.137 --> 00:09:05.905
Musgrave at DoD wants
a briefing.

153
00:09:06.041 --> 00:09:08.106
SCANLON:
Get Wakefield down here now.

154
00:09:08.241 --> 00:09:09.971
Tell Musgrave
it was a minor breach.

155
00:09:10.107 --> 00:09:11.506
Recovery is in process.

156
00:09:11.641 --> 00:09:13.376
Sir. he will not want
to hear it from me.

157
00:09:13.511 --> 00:09:15.511
If I pick up the phone.
it means I'm concerned.

158
00:09:15.647 --> 00:09:17.415
If they even get a whiff
of that. we'll have the entire

159
00:09:17.551 --> 00:09:19.848
military and intelligence
apparatus up here in an hour.

160
00:09:19.983 --> 00:09:21.251
Handle him.

161
00:09:21.386 --> 00:09:22.926
Anything relevant to this
on news feeds?

162
00:09:23.062 --> 00:09:24.261
Not yet.

163
00:09:24.397 --> 00:09:25.997
Socials or secure private?

164
00:09:26.132 --> 00:09:27.698
All quiet.

165
00:09:31.062 --> 00:09:32.934
12 no-shows here today.

166
00:09:36.474 --> 00:09:38.307
All with empty desks.

167
00:09:38.443 --> 00:09:40.704
All clearance above G5.

168
00:09:40.840 --> 00:09:42.878
(busy chatter)

169
00:09:49.383 --> 00:09:52.051
All right. so we're dealing
with an operation

170
00:09:52.186 --> 00:09:55.286
carefully coordinated
and executed.

171
00:09:56.659 --> 00:09:59.297
Why? With what goal?

172
00:09:59.432 --> 00:10:00.895
If they wanted the archive out.

173
00:10:01.031 --> 00:10:02.398
Kellner would have
already released it.

174
00:10:02.534 --> 00:10:03.897
but he hasn't. which means

175
00:10:04.033 --> 00:10:05.704
somebody's maintaining
decision space.

176
00:10:05.839 --> 00:10:09.505
But for how long. we don't know.
so think quickly.

177
00:10:09.641 --> 00:10:11.104
Daniel Kellner has a doctorate

178
00:10:11.239 --> 00:10:12.941
in theoretical
and applied cybersecurity.

179
00:10:13.077 --> 00:10:14.774
and he's spent the better part
of eight years

180
00:10:14.909 --> 00:10:16.405
safeguarding high-side data.

181
00:10:16.540 --> 00:10:18.345
so what does that
tell us about him?

182
00:10:18.480 --> 00:10:19.649
Ideas.

183
00:10:19.784 --> 00:10:20.747
- Come on.
- He built the firewalls.

184
00:10:20.882 --> 00:10:22.480
He knows how to breach them.

185
00:10:22.615 --> 00:10:24.084
They're already breached.
We got to play past that.

186
00:10:24.220 --> 00:10:25.480
AGENT: We got to maintain
standard skip tracing.

187
00:10:25.615 --> 00:10:26.854
AGENT 2:
Well. I can access SYNTRAK.

188
00:10:26.990 --> 00:10:28.423
SERENA:
What's the next thing he does?

189
00:10:28.558 --> 00:10:30.718
BOYD:
Sir.

190
00:10:30.853 --> 00:10:33.698
Hugo Wakefield didn't show up
for work this morning.

191
00:10:35.558 --> 00:10:38.266
(sighs)
His desk was cleaned out.

192
00:10:38.401 --> 00:10:40.001
Hugo?

193
00:10:43.139 --> 00:10:46.276
Second device is missing
from deep storage.

194
00:10:46.411 --> 00:10:48.104
Where's the third?

195
00:10:48.240 --> 00:10:50.011
Locked down in the cold room.

196
00:10:54.077 --> 00:10:56.116
♪ ♪

197
00:11:16.099 --> 00:11:18.138
♪ ♪

198
00:11:25.341 --> 00:11:26.575
(vehicle door closes)

199
00:11:30.747 --> 00:11:33.522
DANIEL: How do you know
they'll answer it?

200
00:11:33.658 --> 00:11:35.353
'Cause that's what we do.

201
00:11:36.353 --> 00:11:38.125
How do you know this place?

202
00:11:42.696 --> 00:11:44.164
Jane.

203
00:11:45.430 --> 00:11:48.234
(sobbing):
Oh... oh. my dear.

204
00:11:52.408 --> 00:11:54.873
The monsignor has finally
surrendered his sneakers.

205
00:11:55.009 --> 00:11:56.340
- Oh.
- (chuckling)

206
00:11:56.475 --> 00:11:57.947
Oh. I couldn't bear
his other shoes.

207
00:11:58.082 --> 00:12:00.283
I know. They always
squeaked so horribly.

208
00:12:00.418 --> 00:12:01.485
(both laughing)

209
00:12:01.620 --> 00:12:04.085
(imitating squeaking footsteps)

210
00:12:04.220 --> 00:12:07.686
Oh. we have missed you
very much. my dear.

211
00:12:07.821 --> 00:12:09.521
Oh. come on.

212
00:12:09.657 --> 00:12:11.389
All I ever did was drive you
and the other sisters crazy.

213
00:12:11.524 --> 00:12:15.096
Mm. well. you do ask
a lot of questions.

214
00:12:15.231 --> 00:12:17.158
Did Teresa ever get through
her postulancy?

215
00:12:17.294 --> 00:12:18.559
She sailed through.

216
00:12:18.695 --> 00:12:20.733
Once she stopped
sneaking out at night.

217
00:12:20.868 --> 00:12:22.301
JANE:
No.

218
00:12:22.437 --> 00:12:23.441
SISTER MAURA:
The monsignor has her teaching

219
00:12:23.577 --> 00:12:25.370
third grade at St. Anthony's.

220
00:12:25.505 --> 00:12:27.708
JANE: Oh. she'll be
fantastic with kids.

221
00:12:27.844 --> 00:12:30.078
BOTH:
Saint Benedicta.

222
00:12:32.684 --> 00:12:35.611
Hold this against your eye.

223
00:12:43.192 --> 00:12:45.396
I'm not going to ask you
any questions.

224
00:12:45.531 --> 00:12:46.923
It's not my business.

225
00:12:47.058 --> 00:12:49.057
But Jane is.

226
00:12:50.060 --> 00:12:53.767
Whatever you have done. you must
hold yourself accountable.

227
00:12:53.903 --> 00:12:56.968
But leave Jane out of it.

228
00:12:57.103 --> 00:12:59.404
She can stay with us.

229
00:13:04.244 --> 00:13:05.916
(chuckling):
You were a nun?

230
00:13:07.315 --> 00:13:09.812
We've had sex.
What do you think?

231
00:13:09.948 --> 00:13:13.451
I think everything you told me
about yourself isn't true.

232
00:13:14.795 --> 00:13:16.824
You have an enormous
amount of nerve.

233
00:13:16.960 --> 00:13:19.063
Yeah. I kept things to myself

234
00:13:19.198 --> 00:13:21.765
because I had to sign away
my life. but your thing...

235
00:13:21.900 --> 00:13:24.598
(chuckles)
You were an actual nun?

236
00:13:24.733 --> 00:13:26.504
A novitiate.

237
00:13:26.639 --> 00:13:27.736
Why didn't you say anything?

238
00:13:27.871 --> 00:13:29.230
I omitted a portion of my story.

239
00:13:29.365 --> 00:13:30.468
People judge you.

240
00:13:33.402 --> 00:13:35.341
When was all this?

241
00:13:36.382 --> 00:13:37.938
Three years ago.

242
00:13:38.074 --> 00:13:41.050
And I'm not answering
any more questions until you do.

243
00:13:42.753 --> 00:13:44.317
What did you steal?

244
00:13:46.750 --> 00:13:49.394
I stole the data
they paid me to protect.

245
00:13:49.529 --> 00:13:51.324
Why would you do that?

246
00:13:52.593 --> 00:13:54.360
'Cause people have a right
to know the truth.

247
00:13:55.594 --> 00:13:58.760
And what is it.
this truth you stole?

248
00:14:00.966 --> 00:14:02.732
So...

249
00:14:02.868 --> 00:14:06.845
you wanted to be a nun.
but what. you lost your faith?

250
00:14:07.843 --> 00:14:09.506
I lost my calling.

251
00:14:09.642 --> 00:14:12.415
How long have you worked
for these people?

252
00:14:12.550 --> 00:14:14.281
Since. um...

253
00:14:18.183 --> 00:14:20.417
Since I got out...

254
00:14:20.553 --> 00:14:22.784
of federal prison
eight years ago.

255
00:14:26.693 --> 00:14:31.200
I did 19 months in Petersburg
for cybercrimes.

256
00:14:31.335 --> 00:14:33.602
WARDEX recruited me
straight out of the parking lot

257
00:14:33.738 --> 00:14:35.598
the day I was released.

258
00:14:35.734 --> 00:14:38.140
- Even with your record?
- Because of my record.

259
00:14:39.206 --> 00:14:40.503
I keep secrets for a living.

260
00:14:40.639 --> 00:14:43.906
I-I didn't mean
to keep them from you.

261
00:14:44.041 --> 00:14:47.578
Three months ago. I didn't know
half of what I know now.

262
00:14:49.212 --> 00:14:50.680
Jane...

