753
00:35:09.099 --> 00:35:10.436
- Maggie. what are you doing?
- Getting dressed.

754
00:35:10.571 --> 00:35:11.699
- We're leaving. We're leaving.
- What?

755
00:35:11.835 --> 00:35:13.075
- Got to go. Got to go.
- What?

756
00:35:13.211 --> 00:35:14.373
- Got to go.
- What are you talk...

757
00:35:14.508 --> 00:35:15.638
- Oh. God. I'm so sorry.
- Hi. Uh...

758
00:35:15.773 --> 00:35:16.913
- Excuse me.
- What do you mean?

759
00:35:17.049 --> 00:35:18.545
- You mean busting out?
- Yep.

760
00:35:18.680 --> 00:35:19.973
- Wh-What's wrong with you?
- What's wrong is I have

761
00:35:20.109 --> 00:35:21.811
a very uncooperative
boyfriend right...

762
00:35:25.281 --> 00:35:27.849
- Oh. you got to be kidding me.
- What? What did I do?

763
00:35:27.984 --> 00:35:29.451
You know exactly
what I'm talking about.

764
00:35:29.586 --> 00:35:31.359
What did I do? Maggie.

765
00:35:32.655 --> 00:35:33.827
Shoes. Shoes. shoes.

766
00:35:33.962 --> 00:35:35.457
Yeah. sure.

767
00:35:35.592 --> 00:35:37.266
- Here.
- Thank you.

768
00:35:39.462 --> 00:35:41.435
How's it going?

769
00:35:49.571 --> 00:35:51.610
♪ ♪

770
00:35:59.591 --> 00:36:01.281
WARDEX?

771
00:36:01.417 --> 00:36:04.821
Stands for Waived Reporting
Development and Extraction.

772
00:36:06.092 --> 00:36:07.659
Of what?

773
00:36:24.811 --> 00:36:28.713
Homestead Air Force Base
in Florida. 1973.

774
00:36:29.812 --> 00:36:31.413
Who's the guy with Nixon?

775
00:36:31.549 --> 00:36:33.219
Big TV star in the '50s.

776
00:36:33.354 --> 00:36:35.225
Nixon wanted to impress him.

777
00:36:44.461 --> 00:36:46.500
♪ ♪

778
00:37:05.988 --> 00:37:08.016
♪ ♪

779
00:37:23.072 --> 00:37:24.771
Are they children?

780
00:37:24.907 --> 00:37:26.408
No.

781
00:37:29.508 --> 00:37:32.438
Are they... people?

782
00:37:32.574 --> 00:37:34.383
No.

783
00:37:37.954 --> 00:37:39.619
Are they human?

784
00:37:52.730 --> 00:37:54.865
This next part's hard to watch.

785
00:37:56.441 --> 00:37:59.232
It's what Hugo showed me
that got me into this.

786
00:38:00.811 --> 00:38:02.004
Okay?

787
00:38:07.884 --> 00:38:09.352
Okay.

788
00:38:10.888 --> 00:38:12.278
(taps key)

789
00:38:12.413 --> 00:38:14.050
MED TECH 1 (on video):
We're gonna need vitals.

790
00:38:14.185 --> 00:38:15.587
- We've got no baseline.
- (overlapping chatter on video)

791
00:38:15.723 --> 00:38:17.151
MED TECH 2:
Pulse ox can't read.

792
00:38:17.287 --> 00:38:18.824
- No standard landmarks...
- MED TECH 3: Ketamine?

793
00:38:18.959 --> 00:38:20.229
- Four to six milligrams?
- SCANLON: No more sedatives.

794
00:38:20.364 --> 00:38:21.926
I want baseline
stress data first.

795
00:38:22.061 --> 00:38:23.929
MED TECH 4: Shift your grip.
Secure the ankles.

796
00:38:24.065 --> 00:38:26.461
- (clicking vocalizations)
- Stabilize head and right arm.

797
00:38:26.596 --> 00:38:28.796
(shrieks)

798
00:38:28.931 --> 00:38:30.800
(distressed shrieking. clicking)

799
00:38:30.936 --> 00:38:32.205
MED TECH 3:
Head's moving too much.

800
00:38:32.341 --> 00:38:33.872
I need a padded restraint.

801
00:38:34.007 --> 00:38:36.036
SCANLON: I have it.
I need cerebrospinal fluid.

802
00:38:36.171 --> 00:38:38.480
Advance the needle
18 centimeters.

803
00:38:38.615 --> 00:38:40.208
- ventral to the medulla.
- (shuddering breaths)

804
00:38:40.344 --> 00:38:42.481
MED TECH 1: It's in distress.
Administering propofol.

805
00:38:42.616 --> 00:38:44.581
SCANLON:
Negative. No anesthesia.

806
00:38:44.716 --> 00:38:46.646
We lost one that way. Do it now.

807
00:38:46.782 --> 00:38:47.989
Insert it now.

808
00:38:48.124 --> 00:38:49.958
(pained shrieking)

809
00:38:50.093 --> 00:38:51.685
(shrieking stops)

810
00:38:51.821 --> 00:38:54.859
(shuddering breaths)

811
00:39:04.107 --> 00:39:05.500
There's more.

812
00:39:05.636 --> 00:39:08.675
79 years more.

813
00:39:10.707 --> 00:39:12.408
I have all of it.

814
00:39:12.543 --> 00:39:15.110
(whirring)

815
00:39:17.418 --> 00:39:19.455
(electronic trilling)

816
00:39:21.123 --> 00:39:23.316
(buzzing)

817
00:39:34.837 --> 00:39:38.035
Hugo is the only one
who had a relationship with it.

818
00:39:38.170 --> 00:39:40.569
and he knew what he was doing
with that thing.

819
00:39:40.705 --> 00:39:42.676
Pull up Kellner's data.

820
00:39:47.976 --> 00:39:49.384
Give me the device.

821
00:39:49.520 --> 00:39:50.979
BOYD:
If systolic goes below 90

822
00:39:51.115 --> 00:39:52.421
like last time.
I'm pulling you out.

823
00:39:52.556 --> 00:39:53.918
MED TECH:
Watch for tachyarrhythmia.

824
00:39:54.053 --> 00:39:55.683
- subdural hemorrhage.
- MED TECH 2: Copy.

825
00:39:55.818 --> 00:39:58.153
(monitor beeping)

826
00:39:59.557 --> 00:40:01.424
(quiet chatter)

827
00:40:01.559 --> 00:40:03.598
♪ ♪

828
00:40:11.439 --> 00:40:14.037
(beeping growing faster)

829
00:40:16.145 --> 00:40:17.275
(whimpers)

830
00:40:17.410 --> 00:40:20.048
(yells. groans)

831
00:40:20.184 --> 00:40:22.280
I'm fine. I'm fine!

832
00:40:22.416 --> 00:40:24.014
What happened?

833
00:40:26.324 --> 00:40:28.555
I had focus. gave myself over.

834
00:40:28.691 --> 00:40:31.422
saw Kellner for a split second.
then...

835
00:40:31.558 --> 00:40:32.988
sledgehammer. whiteout.

836
00:40:33.123 --> 00:40:35.592
Sucked all the air
out of my lungs.

837
00:40:35.727 --> 00:40:37.626
Is he an experiencer?

838
00:40:37.762 --> 00:40:39.392
You can't dive on them.

839
00:40:41.737 --> 00:40:44.071
He can't have been.
I'd have known.

840
00:40:44.206 --> 00:40:45.805
He's Hugo's guy.

841
00:40:45.940 --> 00:40:48.237
There's gonna be a whole lot
we don't know.

842
00:40:48.372 --> 00:40:50.975
Maybe. but I'm not going
back in there to find out.

843
00:41:01.182 --> 00:41:03.251
Pull the data on the girlfriend.

844
00:41:04.752 --> 00:41:08.498
There have been retrieval
programs of exotic craft.

845
00:41:09.567 --> 00:41:12.998
Interrogation
of nonhuman biologics.

846
00:41:13.133 --> 00:41:16.202
Reverse engineering
and technology exploitation.

847
00:41:16.337 --> 00:41:17.836
All of it...

848
00:41:17.971 --> 00:41:20.802
run by WARDEX.
the Department of Defense

849
00:41:20.938 --> 00:41:23.071
and the defense industry.

850
00:41:23.207 --> 00:41:25.612
It has the highest level
of military

851
00:41:25.748 --> 00:41:27.181
and private sector
classification

852
00:41:27.317 --> 00:41:28.645
in American history.

853
00:41:28.780 --> 00:41:30.012
(wind howling outside)

854
00:41:30.148 --> 00:41:31.451
They've run it
since the early '70s

855
00:41:31.586 --> 00:41:32.850
without government funding.

856
00:41:32.986 --> 00:41:34.954
Too many tax dollars
to try and hide.

857
00:41:35.089 --> 00:41:37.450
and-and off-world artifacts
are too profitable

858
00:41:37.585 --> 00:41:39.185
to leave in the hands
of appointed officials.

859
00:41:39.320 --> 00:41:42.060
especially after
the Nixon thing.

860
00:41:42.196 --> 00:41:45.835
Presidents are civilians again
after eight years. so...

861
00:41:45.970 --> 00:41:49.165
so there's no longer a reason
to read them in on any of this.

862
00:41:51.271 --> 00:41:54.511
I was a part of all that
until I saw what you just saw.

863
00:41:55.675 --> 00:41:59.038
This all stops now.

864
00:41:59.173 --> 00:42:00.815
What are you gonna do?

865
00:42:01.818 --> 00:42:06.380
Full disclosure
to the whole world all at once.

866
00:42:09.222 --> 00:42:12.089
Have you considered
what effect that'll have?

867
00:42:13.329 --> 00:42:14.993
On everything?

868
00:42:16.033 --> 00:42:17.357
What...

869
00:42:17.493 --> 00:42:19.195
It's not up to me
to decide if it's...

870
00:42:19.330 --> 00:42:22.166
if it's good or bad
for people to know.

871
00:42:22.301 --> 00:42:25.002
Then how is it up to you
to decide that the right to know

872
00:42:25.138 --> 00:42:27.400
outweighs the consequences
of knowing?

873
00:42:27.536 --> 00:42:29.307
Are you saying
we leave this up to WARDEX?

874
00:42:29.442 --> 00:42:31.843
'Cause they-they've already
decided this belongs to them.

875
00:42:31.979 --> 00:42:34.582
this core truth
about the universe.

876
00:42:34.718 --> 00:42:36.850
- It's wrong.
- You can't do that.

877
00:42:38.013 --> 00:42:39.688
Think about...

878
00:42:41.315 --> 00:42:42.756
People will see them as deities.

879
00:42:42.892 --> 00:42:44.787
- They'll stop believing in God.
- (scoffs)

880
00:42:44.923 --> 00:42:46.691
Well. you left the church.

881
00:42:46.826 --> 00:42:48.224
Not because I stopped believing.

882
00:42:48.359 --> 00:42:49.857
because I could no longer say
with certainty

883
00:42:49.993 --> 00:42:51.359
that God is divine.

884
00:42:51.494 --> 00:42:54.571
but I believe profoundly
that he's essential.

885
00:42:56.331 --> 00:42:57.838
He's how we define ourselves.

886
00:42:57.973 --> 00:43:00.841
He's what keeps
whole civilizations together.

887
00:43:02.407 --> 00:43:05.176
We've been raised to believe
in a supreme being.

888
00:43:05.311 --> 00:43:08.976
and now you want to show us
actual supreme beings?

889
00:43:09.112 --> 00:43:10.818
People can't handle both.

890
00:43:13.390 --> 00:43:15.057
Of course they can.

891
00:43:15.192 --> 00:43:16.682
No. they can't.

892
00:43:17.685 --> 00:43:19.655
Look at our history
with any sudden change.

893
00:43:20.691 --> 00:43:24.964
And now. with the world about
to blow up in all our faces?

894
00:43:26.563 --> 00:43:31.036
You'll get panic and-and chaos.
and God help us.

895
00:43:35.270 --> 00:43:37.405
Hugo's expecting me to check in.

896
00:43:49.226 --> 00:43:50.858
No signal.

897
00:43:52.658 --> 00:43:54.420
No signal.

898
00:43:54.556 --> 00:43:56.666
I'll try the other side
of the hill.

899
00:44:09.974 --> 00:44:12.275
(door opens and closes)

900
00:44:14.243 --> 00:44:16.345
(Jackson grunting. panting)

901
00:44:21.490 --> 00:44:23.517
(thunder rumbling)

902
00:44:26.727 --> 00:44:27.959
- Okay.
- (knocking)

903
00:44:28.095 --> 00:44:29.289
- Unlock the door!
- (engine starts)

904
00:44:29.424 --> 00:44:30.631
- What?
- Jackson. come on!

905
00:44:30.767 --> 00:44:32.427
- (lock clicks)
- Oh. shit. Sorry.

906
00:44:33.601 --> 00:44:35.304
Oh. sorry. sorry.

907
00:44:35.440 --> 00:44:37.839
- Okay.
- Oh. my God.

908
00:44:39.639 --> 00:44:42.002
(phone ringing)

909
00:44:42.137 --> 00:44:43.537
(Jackson stammers)

910
00:44:43.672 --> 00:44:45.174
If you answer that in French.
I swear to God

911
00:44:45.309 --> 00:44:46.576
I'm marching you
right back inside.

912
00:44:46.711 --> 00:44:48.246
Hello?

913
00:44:48.381 --> 00:44:50.210
HUGO (over phone): I've been
waiting a very long time

914
00:44:50.345 --> 00:44:52.517
to meet you. Ms. Fairchild.

915
00:44:52.652 --> 00:44:54.090
Who is this?

916
00:44:54.225 --> 00:44:55.857
A friend.

917
00:44:57.092 --> 00:44:59.789
And if I'm right about you.
Margaret.

918
00:44:59.925 --> 00:45:01.320
you'd know if I wasn't.

919
00:45:01.455 --> 00:45:02.864
No. I don't... I don't know you

920
00:45:02.999 --> 00:45:04.692
any more than I know
what's happening to me.

921
00:45:04.828 --> 00:45:07.034
HUGO: Very few people could
manage this as well as you.

922
00:45:07.169 --> 00:45:08.870
- I'm not managing it. I'm not.
- Who-who is that?

923
00:45:09.005 --> 00:45:11.302
I am frightened.
I'm frightened out of my wits.

924
00:45:11.437 --> 00:45:15.404
Because you're just a passenger
on your way somewhere.

925
00:45:15.539 --> 00:45:17.246
- Let us help you get there.
- Help me how?

926
00:45:17.381 --> 00:45:18.404
What do you mean?

927
00:45:18.539 --> 00:45:19.880
- Is that the FBI?
- Shh!

928
00:45:20.016 --> 00:45:21.043
HUGO: We want to offer you
our protection.

929
00:45:21.178 --> 00:45:22.542
We held back on reaching out

930
00:45:22.678 --> 00:45:24.615
until after we saw
your weather report.

931
00:45:24.751 --> 00:45:26.084
You held back?

932
00:45:26.220 --> 00:45:27.214
What do you mean?
What does that mean?

933
00:45:27.349 --> 00:45:29.154
Are you gonna need a lawyer?

934
00:45:32.890 --> 00:45:35.765
Who is 873-2626?

935
00:45:37.458 --> 00:45:38.834
Since you know that number.

936
00:45:38.969 --> 00:45:41.232
you must already know
who it belongs to.

937
00:45:43.570 --> 00:45:44.807
Kellner?

938
00:45:45.836 --> 00:45:46.736
Kellner?

939
00:45:46.871 --> 00:45:48.607
All right.

940
00:45:48.742 --> 00:45:50.235
Listen carefully.

941
00:45:50.371 --> 00:45:51.714
You cannot go home.

942
00:45:51.850 --> 00:45:53.111
If you have another direction
in mind.

943
00:45:53.246 --> 00:45:55.311
even a vague inclination.
follow it.

944
00:45:55.447 --> 00:45:57.149
If we can find you by phone.
others can

945
00:45:57.284 --> 00:45:59.017
- find you in the world.
- No. it's too late.

946
00:45:59.152 --> 00:46:00.515
They...
Uh. they already found me.

947
00:46:00.650 --> 00:46:03.249
Hang up immediately.
Destroy your phone.

948
00:46:03.384 --> 00:46:04.726
How will you find me?

949
00:46:04.862 --> 00:46:06.085
I have every confidence
you'll find us.

950
00:46:06.220 --> 00:46:07.258
Do it now.

951
00:46:09.066 --> 00:46:11.867
Wait. wait. What are you...
Wh-What are you doing?!

952
00:46:13.504 --> 00:46:14.435
Back up over the phone.

953
00:46:14.571 --> 00:46:16.303
- What?
- Back up!

954
00:46:16.438 --> 00:46:18.006
- Come on.
- Okay. I'd like
to point out that I'm being

955
00:46:18.142 --> 00:46:20.266
extremely cool here
and that I'm rolling with it.

956
00:46:20.402 --> 00:46:22.441
and that was a $600 phone.

957
00:46:23.444 --> 00:46:25.343
Well. it's still a $600 phone
'cause you missed it.

958
00:46:25.478 --> 00:46:26.844
Jackson. pull forward
till you hear the crunch.

959
00:46:26.979 --> 00:46:28.015
- Come on.
- Sorry.

960
00:46:32.550 --> 00:46:34.654
Oh. my God. you missed it again.
Oh. my God.

961
00:46:34.790 --> 00:46:36.826
- Okay. (mutters)
- What?

962
00:46:40.594 --> 00:46:41.930
Okay.

963
00:46:43.601 --> 00:46:46.000
Pull forward. Go. go. go.

964
00:46:47.604 --> 00:46:49.366
Keep going. Keep going.

965
00:46:58.646 --> 00:47:00.948
Okay. Okay.

966
00:47:01.084 --> 00:47:04.320
- Okay. let's go. Let's go.
- Uh... wh-where?

967
00:47:04.455 --> 00:47:05.986
- North.
- Why?

968
00:47:06.122 --> 00:47:07.312
Because that's where
Daniel Kellner is.

969
00:47:07.448 --> 00:47:08.991
Oh. my God. (stammering)

970
00:47:09.126 --> 00:47:10.685
Who is this dude?
Is he some guy from your past

971
00:47:10.821 --> 00:47:12.257
- that you never told me about?
- I don't know. Jackson.

972
00:47:12.392 --> 00:47:13.586
- Or what is it?
- You're giving me a headache.

973
00:47:13.722 --> 00:47:14.495
I don't know
what I'm doing here.

974
00:47:14.631 --> 00:47:15.863
I don't know who he is.

975
00:47:15.999 --> 00:47:17.460
I just know
he's someplace north.

976
00:47:17.596 --> 00:47:18.534
- That's all I know. okay?
- (hailstones clacking)

977
00:47:18.669 --> 00:47:20.001
Oh. my God. What is that sound?

978
00:47:22.431 --> 00:47:24.471
- Your hailstorm.
- Wow.

979
00:47:24.606 --> 00:47:25.902
Weather Shimmy?

980
00:47:26.038 --> 00:47:28.306
Just drive. Just drive.

981
00:47:37.986 --> 00:47:40.289
(electronic trilling. beeping)

982
00:47:40.424 --> 00:47:42.452
♪ ♪

983
00:48:08.143 --> 00:48:09.886
(sighs)

984
00:48:10.852 --> 00:48:12.213
(electronic warbling)

985
00:48:12.348 --> 00:48:14.319
(crate thuds on table)

986
00:48:16.825 --> 00:48:19.357
You got Kellner on 2626.

987
00:48:21.064 --> 00:48:22.622
Look at the video
I just sent you.

988
00:48:22.758 --> 00:48:24.131
DANIEL (over phone):
Okay. hold on.

989
00:48:26.267 --> 00:48:28.300
(Margaret clicking tongue
on video)

990
00:48:30.606 --> 00:48:32.038
Yeah. So?

991
00:48:32.174 --> 00:48:33.971
She's the one
we've been waiting for.

992
00:48:34.106 --> 00:48:36.435
DANIEL:
Her? Why?

993
00:48:36.570 --> 00:48:38.845
Did you not hear her?

994
00:48:38.981 --> 00:48:40.340
DANIEL:
Yeah. I heard her.

995
00:48:40.475 --> 00:48:41.784
And you still ask why?

996
00:48:41.920 --> 00:48:43.684
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

997
00:48:43.820 --> 00:48:45.581
That's all she had to say?

998
00:48:47.024 --> 00:48:49.019
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

999
00:48:49.154 --> 00:48:50.415
That's what she said?

1000
00:48:50.551 --> 00:48:52.093
You didn't hear it?

1001
00:48:53.563 --> 00:48:55.063
We all heard it.

1002
00:48:55.199 --> 00:48:57.293
We couldn't understand it.
It's not English.

1003
00:48:57.428 --> 00:48:58.964
(chuckling):
Of course it is.

1004
00:48:59.100 --> 00:49:00.993
I'm listening to it right now.

1005
00:49:01.128 --> 00:49:02.930
I'm sending you to Kansas City.
where she's from.

1006
00:49:03.066 --> 00:49:04.932
- We'll get a car to you.
Leave tonight.
- Hey. wait.

1007
00:49:05.067 --> 00:49:06.603
- Wait a second. Wait a second.
- Do not travel by day.

1008
00:49:06.738 --> 00:49:08.042
You're not hearing it?
It's-it's perfectly clear.

1009
00:49:08.177 --> 00:49:09.139
Detour past tollbooths
and turnpikes.

1010
00:49:09.275 --> 00:49:10.472
DANIEL:
Hey. listen to me.

1011
00:49:10.608 --> 00:49:11.710
Have you played this
to other people?

1012
00:49:11.846 --> 00:49:13.776
Stay with me.

1013
00:49:13.911 --> 00:49:16.545
A motel room key will be
in the car with directions.

1014
00:49:16.681 --> 00:49:18.480
Santiago will retrieve you
in the morning.

1015
00:49:18.615 --> 00:49:21.023
By then. I'll know
what comes next.

1016
00:49:21.158 --> 00:49:23.758
Hugo. you're scaring
the shit out of me.

1017
00:49:23.894 --> 00:49:27.491
There are two of you. Daniel.

1018
00:49:27.626 --> 00:49:30.762
There's always been
just the two of you.

1019
00:49:30.897 --> 00:49:32.764
(rustling)

1020
00:49:32.899 --> 00:49:34.927
♪ ♪

1021
00:49:59.092 --> 00:50:00.821
(breathing heavily)

1022
00:50:02.324 --> 00:50:04.396
(pills rattling)

1023
00:50:10.134 --> 00:50:12.706
(gasping)

1024
00:50:12.842 --> 00:50:15.143
(trembling breaths)

1025
00:50:20.078 --> 00:50:21.446
(exhales slowly)

1026
00:50:24.184 --> 00:50:26.220
(trembling breaths continue)

1027
00:50:27.789 --> 00:50:29.520
(whirring)

1028
00:50:40.197 --> 00:50:42.698
♪ ♪

1029
00:50:43.807 --> 00:50:46.141
