(rocks clattering)

1264
01:05:18.877 --> 01:05:20.773
(panting)

1265
01:05:31.691 --> 01:05:33.060
Run!

1266
01:05:34.059 --> 01:05:35.458
JANE:
Wait!

1267
01:05:37.067 --> 01:05:39.429
- What are you doing?
- Put it in drive!

1268
01:05:59.555 --> 01:06:01.581
(urgent chatter)

1269
01:06:01.717 --> 01:06:03.521
- You see them?
- You got a visual?

1270
01:06:03.657 --> 01:06:05.125
- Anybody got eyes on anything?
- They must have gone over.

1271
01:06:05.260 --> 01:06:06.787
Requesting underwater search
and recovery

1272
01:06:06.922 --> 01:06:08.193
- on site right now.
- They're down. They're down.

1273
01:06:08.328 --> 01:06:10.022
They're down.
They're in the water.

1274
01:06:10.158 --> 01:06:11.426
Can we get a team down there
and see if we can find them?

1275
01:06:11.562 --> 01:06:12.799
- We need some divers.
- Down there.

1276
01:06:12.934 --> 01:06:15.062
(chatter continues indistinctly)

1277
01:06:15.197 --> 01:06:17.164
(horns honking)

1278
01:06:17.299 --> 01:06:19.337
(panicked chatter)

1279
01:06:36.159 --> 01:06:37.716
They all think
the world's going to hell.

1280
01:06:37.852 --> 01:06:39.320
Got to get going now.
Jackson. okay?

1281
01:06:39.455 --> 01:06:40.686
Daniel Kellner's gonna be there.

1282
01:06:40.822 --> 01:06:42.361
Not right now.
but he will be soon.

1283
01:06:42.496 --> 01:06:43.989
- We got to go north.
- No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

1284
01:06:44.124 --> 01:06:45.961
- Got to go north right now.
- No. we need to...

1285
01:06:46.096 --> 01:06:47.763
- We need to go back
to the hospital.
- No. no. no. Jack.

1286
01:06:47.899 --> 01:06:48.835
This is not something you
get treated for. It's not...

1287
01:06:48.970 --> 01:06:50.534
You know what's wrong with you.

1288
01:06:50.670 --> 01:06:52.100
is that you think there's
something wrong with me.

1289
01:06:52.236 --> 01:06:54.108
Look at me. Look at me.

1290
01:06:56.009 --> 01:06:57.837
If I moved. you'd stay.

1291
01:06:59.013 --> 01:07:00.377
- What?
- Kansas City.

1292
01:07:00.513 --> 01:07:02.578
You want me to move.
You're gonna stay.

1293
01:07:22.769 --> 01:07:24.238
(sighs)

1294
01:07:24.373 --> 01:07:27.069
You know. this thing
that's happening. it's...

1295
01:07:27.205 --> 01:07:28.906
(takes deep breath)

1296
01:07:29.042 --> 01:07:30.338
It's not coming from me.

1297
01:07:30.473 --> 01:07:33.009
It's like I'm just a passenger.

1298
01:07:33.145 --> 01:07:34.507
That's not a bad thing.

1299
01:07:34.642 --> 01:07:36.942
It's. like. a really good thing.

1300
01:07:38.020 --> 01:07:39.877
- It's like your music.
- Uh-huh.

1301
01:07:40.013 --> 01:07:42.249
You know when you're
in the flow?

1302
01:07:42.385 --> 01:07:44.455
And it just feels...

1303
01:07:46.387 --> 01:07:48.088
I'm in the flow.

1304
01:07:48.223 --> 01:07:49.258
Okay.

1305
01:07:49.393 --> 01:07:50.724
And I told you I'd tell you

1306
01:07:50.860 --> 01:07:54.095
when I get where
I'm supposed to be. and...

1307
01:07:54.230 --> 01:07:55.835
this is it.

1308
01:07:55.971 --> 01:07:57.862
- Okay.
- Right here.

1309
01:07:57.997 --> 01:08:00.704
- It's where I'm supposed to be.
- Okay.

1310
01:08:00.840 --> 01:08:03.641
S-So...

1311
01:08:03.777 --> 01:08:08.606
we need to go north because
that's where Daniel Kellner is?

1312
01:08:08.741 --> 01:08:10.709
Sorry. No. He's east.

1313
01:08:10.844 --> 01:08:12.314
- Oh. And...
- He's east now.

1314
01:08:12.449 --> 01:08:14.088
How do you know that it's east?

1315
01:08:14.224 --> 01:08:17.388
It's just. I have
this vague inclination.

1316
01:08:17.524 --> 01:08:19.089
But he's east now.
He's somewhere east.

1317
01:08:19.225 --> 01:08:21.855
And where is "somewhere"?

1318
01:08:23.723 --> 01:08:25.529
You want me to drive?

1319
01:08:27.197 --> 01:08:28.796
I need a water.

1320
01:08:35.878 --> 01:08:37.310
(entry bell jingling)

1321
01:08:42.442 --> 01:08:43.749
Hey.

1322
01:08:43.884 --> 01:08:45.681
Hello. Hi.

1323
01:08:46.656 --> 01:08:48.750
Hi. Um...

1324
01:08:51.058 --> 01:08:52.521
Will you do me a favor?

1325
01:08:52.657 --> 01:08:54.429
- Dr. Coleman?
- (lively chatter)

1326
01:08:54.564 --> 01:08:56.521
Uh. uh. yes. yes. Thank you.
thank you for taking the call.

1327
01:08:56.657 --> 01:08:58.498
Uh. I-I don't know.

1328
01:08:58.634 --> 01:09:02.362
She just took off. and y-y-yes.
it's getting worse. much worse.

1329
01:09:02.498 --> 01:09:03.770
Yes. please. Thank you.

1330
01:09:03.906 --> 01:09:05.001
Yes. Hold on one second.

1331
01:09:05.136 --> 01:09:06.403
Excuse me. sir.

1332
01:09:06.539 --> 01:09:07.907
Do you know the address
around here?

1333
01:09:08.043 --> 01:09:10.145
37 Pearl Street. Decatur.

1334
01:09:11.112 --> 01:09:14.144
37 Pearl Street. Decatur.

1335
01:09:14.280 --> 01:09:16.014
We'll be here. Thank you.

1336
01:09:16.149 --> 01:09:17.614
(entry bell jingling)

1337
01:09:26.930 --> 01:09:28.661
BOY:
Hey. mister.

1338
01:09:29.664 --> 01:09:33.366
She said to say she loves you.
but she's going east.

1339
01:09:49.477 --> 01:09:50.977
Why Kansas City?

1340
01:09:51.113 --> 01:09:54.187
Best to focus on
getting you there tomorrow.

1341
01:09:54.322 --> 01:09:56.719
DANIEL (panting):
Hugo. I'm...

1342
01:09:58.522 --> 01:10:00.158
Uh. it's coming back to me.

1343
01:10:00.294 --> 01:10:02.058
Things are coming back to me.

1344
01:10:02.193 --> 01:10:03.497
What things?

1345
01:10:03.633 --> 01:10:05.332
Animals.

1346
01:10:05.467 --> 01:10:08.665
Friendly. terrifying animals
looking at me.

1347
01:10:10.363 --> 01:10:13.371
And you can't look away
no matter how hard you try?

1348
01:10:13.507 --> 01:10:16.068
No. no.
They have to look away first.

1349
01:10:18.872 --> 01:10:21.513
Is this a memory or a dream?

1350
01:10:22.512 --> 01:10:24.148
I can't tell anymore.

1351
01:10:24.283 --> 01:10:26.485
(shower water running)

1352
01:10:28.484 --> 01:10:30.082
HUGO:
Daniel?

1353
01:10:32.189 --> 01:10:33.657
Daniel.

1354
01:10:34.697 --> 01:10:36.088
Daniel.

1355
01:10:36.223 --> 01:10:38.356
It wasn't your idea
to recruit me. was it?

1356
01:10:38.492 --> 01:10:41.797
Not just for this but-but
to WARDEX in the first place.

1357
01:10:44.500 --> 01:10:46.037
No. it wasn't.

1358
01:10:46.173 --> 01:10:48.539
And there was a reason?

1359
01:10:48.674 --> 01:10:50.872
A specific reason
why you wanted me?

1360
01:10:52.515 --> 01:10:55.811
Other than your prodigious gift
for numbers? Yes.

1361
01:10:56.881 --> 01:10:59.645
You decided to keep
all of this to yourself?

1362
01:10:59.781 --> 01:11:02.781
Because I care about you.

1363
01:11:02.917 --> 01:11:04.721
Because you have a job to do.

1364
01:11:04.856 --> 01:11:08.395
And nothing can get
in the way of that.

1365
01:11:11.165 --> 01:11:13.191
There's parts of me...

1366
01:11:15.198 --> 01:11:18.365
...from when I was a kid
that I should be able to know.

1367
01:11:18.500 --> 01:11:20.132
and I don't.

1368
01:11:23.704 --> 01:11:25.280
They're just gone.

1369
01:11:26.245 --> 01:11:28.283
I'm so scared.

1370
01:11:29.579 --> 01:11:31.546
You don't need to be.

1371
01:11:31.682 --> 01:11:34.413
You have me and someone else.

1372
01:11:34.548 --> 01:11:38.391
And when the time is right.
everything will become clear.

1373
01:11:38.527 --> 01:11:41.094
Daniel. there's a place
you'll need to be

1374
01:11:41.229 --> 01:11:43.155
in the morning without fail.

1375
01:11:43.290 --> 01:11:46.026
There will be no other day
like tomorrow.

1376
01:11:48.929 --> 01:11:51.339
Where do you need me to go?

1377
01:11:53.600 --> 01:11:55.600
KCXE?

1378
01:11:55.735 --> 01:11:57.510
What's KCXE?

1379
01:12:38.311 --> 01:12:40.387
Danny. I'm gonna ask you
to do something.

1380
01:12:40.523 --> 01:12:42.189
(Margaret speaking indistinctly
on video)

1381
01:12:42.324 --> 01:12:44.249
I want you first
to look at this.

1382
01:12:45.286 --> 01:12:47.560
(Margaret speaking
unintelligibly on video)

1383
01:12:48.827 --> 01:12:50.497
Do you understand
what she's saying?

1384
01:12:51.696 --> 01:12:53.495
I hear her. It-it's gibberish.

1385
01:12:53.630 --> 01:12:55.162
I can't understand it.

1386
01:12:55.297 --> 01:12:59.004
Okay. I-I just heard this
for the first time.

1387
01:12:59.139 --> 01:13:00.405
and I can.

1388
01:13:00.540 --> 01:13:02.070
- It's English.
- English?

1389
01:13:02.205 --> 01:13:04.242
I mean. it's-it's math
turned English in my head.

1390
01:13:04.377 --> 01:13:05.974
translated into words.

1391
01:13:06.977 --> 01:13:10.274
When I look at this.
I hear this.

1392
01:13:10.409 --> 01:13:13.388
(Margaret clicking tongue
on video)

1393
01:13:14.853 --> 01:13:17.183
Danny. I'm gonna ask you
to do something.

1394
01:13:26.235 --> 01:13:27.897
You can't trust me anymore.

1395
01:13:31.298 --> 01:13:33.331
- (insects chirping)
- (sign creaking)

1396
01:13:46.913 --> 01:13:48.280
(gasps softly)

1397
01:13:49.882 --> 01:13:51.252
(hisses in pain)

1398
01:13:51.388 --> 01:13:53.586
(sighs)

1399
01:13:53.721 --> 01:13:55.595
(whimpers)

1400
01:14:01.762 --> 01:14:03.801
♪ ♪

1401
01:14:23.553 --> 01:14:25.592
♪ ♪

1402
01:14:40.237 --> 01:14:42.138
- (breathing heavily)
- (monitor beeping steadily)

1403
01:14:42.274 --> 01:14:44.006
Got him.

1404
01:14:46.311 --> 01:14:48.274
(groans)

1405
01:14:52.780 --> 01:14:54.819
(engine revving)

1406
01:15:12.306 --> 01:15:14.674
(engines revving)

1407
01:15:23.009 --> 01:15:24.849
(tires squealing)

1408
01:15:26.121 --> 01:15:28.149
(Daniel gasping)

1409
01:15:30.587 --> 01:15:33.022
(urgent chatter)

1410
01:15:35.694 --> 01:15:37.121
- They're here.
- (gasps)

1411
01:15:37.256 --> 01:15:38.530
- They're here.
- What?

1412
01:15:38.665 --> 01:15:40.825
- Take that end.
- Go. go. go.

1413
01:15:40.960 --> 01:15:42.900
(panting)

1414
01:15:44.333 --> 01:15:47.003
- The backpack. The backpack!
- You first.

1415
01:15:50.478 --> 01:15:52.503
(urgent chatter continues)

1416
01:15:59.549 --> 01:16:00.616
Come on.

1417
01:16:00.751 --> 01:16:03.014
This is all I've got.

1418
01:16:03.149 --> 01:16:04.523
You're coming. right?

1419
01:16:04.658 --> 01:16:05.916
- (banging at door)
- Shit.

1420
01:16:06.052 --> 01:16:07.221
Breach! Here!

1421
01:16:08.196 --> 01:16:09.796
(urgent chatter)

1422
01:16:09.931 --> 01:16:11.055
- No. come on. come on. come on.
- You got to take this.

1423
01:16:11.191 --> 01:16:12.866
(urgent chatter continues)

1424
01:16:13.001 --> 01:16:16.034
And for God's sake. Jane.
don't touch what's inside.

1425
01:16:16.170 --> 01:16:17.094
Go. Go.

1426
01:16:17.230 --> 01:16:19.266
(urgent chatter continues)

1427
01:16:23.172 --> 01:16:25.580
- (grunting)
- Get out of there!

1428
01:16:32.078 --> 01:16:33.753
Get on the ground!

1429
01:16:36.587 --> 01:16:38.186
They're burned.

1430
01:16:40.989 --> 01:16:42.553
(breathing heavily)

1431
01:16:42.688 --> 01:16:44.731
(agents shouting indistinctly
in distance)

1432
01:16:54.441 --> 01:16:56.072
It's not here.

1433
01:17:00.943 --> 01:17:02.441
Where's the device?

1434
01:17:07.650 --> 01:17:09.146
(sighs)

1435
01:17:09.282 --> 01:17:11.318
<i>(jet engine whirring)</i>

1436
01:17:19.168 --> 01:17:21.196
♪ ♪

1437
01:17:43.649 --> 01:17:45.021
SCANLON:
You've been misled. Daniel.

1438
01:17:45.157 --> 01:17:47.788
We can talk another time
about how hurtful

1439
01:17:47.924 --> 01:17:49.327
all this has been to me.

1440
01:17:49.462 --> 01:17:51.990
but here we are.

1441
01:17:52.126 --> 01:17:53.767
The archive's safe.

1442
01:17:53.902 --> 01:17:56.161
And now you're going
to tell me the name

1443
01:17:56.297 --> 01:17:58.069
of every confederate at WARDEX

1444
01:17:58.204 --> 01:18:00.741
and what exactly
Hugo's operation is planning.

1445
01:18:01.778 --> 01:18:04.811
But first.
without all this nonsense...

1446
01:18:07.710 --> 01:18:10.410
...you're going to tell me
what you did with the device.

1447
01:18:13.652 --> 01:18:15.855
(tires squealing)

1448
01:18:16.852 --> 01:18:18.891
♪ ♪

1449
01:18:29.701 --> 01:18:31.233
(tires squeal)

1450
01:18:33.603 --> 01:18:35.871
The hell do you think
you're doing driving like that?

1451
01:18:36.006 --> 01:18:38.372
You are Agent Thomas Farley.

1452
01:18:38.507 --> 01:18:41.710
Your ten-digit I.D. code is
3893398887.

1453
01:18:41.846 --> 01:18:43.817
What's the day code?

1454
01:18:44.979 --> 01:18:46.644
Kentucky filly.

1455
01:18:49.182 --> 01:18:51.088
(tires squealing)

1456
01:19:01.494 --> 01:19:03.032
- Agent Grady?
- Yes. ma'am.

1457
01:19:03.168 --> 01:19:04.732
Kentucky filly.
Mr. Scanlon sent for me.

1458
01:19:04.867 --> 01:19:06.202
Follow me.

1459
01:19:10.170 --> 01:19:11.871
(engine shuts off)

1460
01:19:12.006 --> 01:19:14.045
♪ ♪

1461
01:19:32.763 --> 01:19:34.802
♪ ♪

1462
01:19:51.353 --> 01:19:52.611
You're her.

1463
01:19:59.088 --> 01:20:01.356
Margaret Fairchild.

1464
01:20:20.909 --> 01:20:22.377
Jocelyn.

1465
01:20:28.257 --> 01:20:29.681
Jocelyn.

1466
01:20:36.925 --> 01:20:38.364
(gasps)

1467
01:20:38.499 --> 01:20:39.794
(grunting)

1468
01:20:39.929 --> 01:20:40.960
Leave her!

1469
01:20:41.095 --> 01:20:42.595
Stand down.

1470
01:21:00.620 --> 01:21:02.890
I know you.

1471
01:21:13.798 --> 01:21:16.062
I know you. too.

1472
01:21:16.198 --> 01:21:18.000
There's two coming out.

1473
01:21:18.136 --> 01:21:19.764
Don't allow them off the base.

1474
01:21:23.074 --> 01:21:25.605
Hey. Hey. Hey. back inside.

1475
01:21:25.741 --> 01:21:27.371
MARGARET: I've waited
too long to tell you.

1476
01:21:27.506 --> 01:21:29.015
and now it's too late.

1477
01:21:30.147 --> 01:21:33.019
But I loved you like my own son.

1478
01:21:36.382 --> 01:21:38.520
Stop. Stop. Stop.

1479
01:21:39.523 --> 01:21:41.092
They said we could go up
to the lake on Friday.

1480
01:21:41.228 --> 01:21:43.053
and-and Grandma and Grandpa
will be there.

1481
01:21:43.189 --> 01:21:47.433
and-and Uncle Howard and Bobby
and Teresa and everybody.

1482
01:21:47.568 --> 01:21:49.596
♪ ♪

1483
01:21:59.573 --> 01:22:01.240
How do you know these people?

1484
01:22:01.376 --> 01:22:02.880
MARGARET:
I don't.

1485
01:22:03.016 --> 01:22:04.743
You were just talking to them.

1486
01:22:10.520 --> 01:22:11.988
I don't understand
what's happening.

1487
01:22:12.124 --> 01:22:13.884
MARGARET:
Just get in!

1488
01:22:20.265 --> 01:22:22.728
- What did you see?
- (engine starts)

1489
01:22:23.867 --> 01:22:25.731
My wife.

1490
01:22:30.104 --> 01:22:31.770
My God.

1491
01:22:32.811 --> 01:22:34.410
What is she?

1492
01:22:35.781 --> 01:22:37.450
Unstoppable.

1493
01:22:37.585 --> 01:22:39.811
♪ ♪

1494
01:22:42.524 --> 01:22:43.958
(beeping)

1495
01:22:49.194 --> 01:22:50.587
DANIEL:
Where are you taking us?

1496
01:22:50.723 --> 01:22:52.566
MARGARET:
Kansas City.

1497
01:22:52.701 --> 01:22:54.067
DANIEL:
Why there?

1498
01:22:54.202 --> 01:22:55.927
- I have to.
- You don't have to go so...

1499
01:22:56.062 --> 01:22:57.996
- Yeah. uh. yeah. I do.
- Uh. you're enjoying this.

1500
01:22:58.132 --> 01:23:00.667
Yeah. I mean. it-it feels good.
It feels good. and then...

1501
01:23:00.802 --> 01:23:02.768
Yeah. but-but... but you know.
You know.

1502
01:23:02.903 --> 01:23:04.403
I mean. you've been driving
like a maniac

1503
01:23:04.538 --> 01:23:05.936
the last few days. you know.

1504
01:23:06.071 --> 01:23:07.809
- How do you know that?
- I just know things.

1505
01:23:07.944 --> 01:23:09.340
It's just. something happened
to me a couple of days ago.

1506
01:23:09.476 --> 01:23:11.380
and now I-I know things.

1507
01:23:11.515 --> 01:23:12.810
Things I don't really
want to know.

1508
01:23:12.945 --> 01:23:14.017
and all the things
I do want to know.

1509
01:23:14.152 --> 01:23:15.483
I don't really know at all.

1510
01:23:15.619 --> 01:23:17.057
so I've just been
kind of rolling with it.

1511
01:23:17.193 --> 01:23:18.651
You know. like...
Oh. wow. you were in jail?

1512
01:23:18.786 --> 01:23:20.325
- That must have been so...
- Hey. hey!

1513
01:23:20.460 --> 01:23:22.056
- (tires squealing)
- MARGARET: You see what I mean?

1514
01:23:22.192 --> 01:23:24.329
It's crazy. It's crazy.

1515
01:23:24.464 --> 01:23:28.201
I look at somebody.
and I just drop in on them.

1516
01:23:29.204 --> 01:23:31.862
It's like. for a few seconds.
I am them.

1517
01:23:31.997 --> 01:23:33.634
I see the things
that they've lived.

1518
01:23:33.770 --> 01:23:35.741
It's just like
it's all happening to me. too.

1519
01:23:35.876 --> 01:23:37.308
You know. like-like...

1520
01:23:37.443 --> 01:23:38.803
like right now
your shoulder's killing you.

1521
01:23:38.938 --> 01:23:40.677
Yeah. and you-you just
want to yell.

1522
01:23:40.812 --> 01:23:42.314
- "Keep your eyes on the road!"
- Keep your eyes on the road!

1523
01:23:42.449 --> 01:23:43.975
I know. and you can't stop
thinking about Jane.

1524
01:23:44.110 --> 01:23:45.214
and Jane should be back
at the Monastery St. Clare.

1525
01:23:45.350 --> 01:23:46.846
- You're absolutely right.
- Jane?

1526
01:23:46.981 --> 01:23:49.386
But then yesterday.
I'm driving with Jackson.

1527
01:23:49.521 --> 01:23:51.453
and I flashed on you
without seeing you.

1528
01:23:51.589 --> 01:23:53.022
(makes whooshing sound)
It was so strong.

1529
01:23:53.158 --> 01:23:54.689
I dropped right in on you

1530
01:23:54.824 --> 01:23:56.394
without even needing
to look at you. and that was

1531
01:23:56.530 --> 01:23:58.162
the first time that crazy shit
has ever happened to me.

1532
01:23:58.298 --> 01:23:59.829
How long you been able
to do this?

1533
01:23:59.964 --> 01:24:01.127
Since yesterday.

1534
01:24:01.262 --> 01:24:02.869
Since the bird.

1535
01:24:03.004 --> 01:24:04.462
- What bird?
- This-this bird.

1536
01:24:04.598 --> 01:24:06.140
Flew in through my window.

1537
01:24:06.275 --> 01:24:08.069
It was beautiful. I looked
at it. and then it-it...

1538
01:24:08.204 --> 01:24:09.170
Was it a cardinal?

1539
01:24:09.305 --> 01:24:10.535
Holy sh... How the...

1540
01:24:10.670 --> 01:24:12.045
You're freaking me the fuck out.

1541
01:24:12.181 --> 01:24:15.049
- (tires squealing)
- (crossing bell dinging)

1542
01:24:18.183 --> 01:24:19.548
I was 20. I was in college.

1543
01:24:19.683 --> 01:24:21.447
You were flunking out.
basically. right?

1544
01:24:21.582 --> 01:24:22.879
Yeah. I-I was pretty smart.

1545
01:24:23.015 --> 01:24:24.287
You were. but it was
the partying.

1546
01:24:24.422 --> 01:24:25.385
It was the partying
and the drugs.

1547
01:24:25.520 --> 01:24:26.951
I mean. ketamine? Come on. dude.

1548
01:24:27.086 --> 01:24:28.357
- Could you please stop?
- Sorry. I'm stopping.

1549
01:24:28.493 --> 01:24:29.620
- I was 20. I was in college.
- Yes.

1550
01:24:29.755 --> 01:24:32.363
Uh. it was dark. I-I was in bed.

1551
01:24:32.499 --> 01:24:34.726
and I dreamed that
something was watching me.

1552
01:24:34.861 --> 01:24:36.365
I woke up.
and there was this bird.

1553
01:24:36.501 --> 01:24:37.795
- It was a cardinal.
- In the window.

1554
01:24:37.931 --> 01:24:39.738
and it-it looked at me.
and after that.

1555
01:24:39.874 --> 01:24:41.339
everything just changed.

1556
01:24:41.474 --> 01:24:43.775
I saw things:
context. patterns. artifacting.

1557
01:24:43.911 --> 01:24:45.509
I could see it all.

1558
01:24:45.644 --> 01:24:47.407
Arrays and conditionals
just appeared in my head...

1559
01:24:47.543 --> 01:24:48.946
Fully solved. "If P. then Q."

1560
01:24:49.082 --> 01:24:50.580
Exactly. Solved equations

1561
01:24:50.715 --> 01:24:52.119
- without even thinking...
- And you could read

1562
01:24:52.254 --> 01:24:53.348
eight-bit binary data
like it was English.

1563
01:24:53.483 --> 01:24:54.512
- like it was nothing.
- Yeah.

1564
01:24:54.648 --> 01:24:55.621
How do you know all this?

1565
01:24:55.756 --> 01:24:57.283
I don't. You do.

1566
01:24:57.418 --> 01:24:58.549
God. you hated it.

1567
01:24:58.685 --> 01:25:00.354
- It was a curse.
- Yeah.

1568
01:25:00.490 --> 01:25:02.186
I couldn't relate to anybody.

1569
01:25:02.322 --> 01:25:03.955
I lost every friend I ever had
because I-I couldn't stand

1570
01:25:04.091 --> 01:25:05.632
- to be around people.
- (train horn blaring)

1571
01:25:05.768 --> 01:25:07.365
Until you met Jane.

1572
01:25:08.766 --> 01:25:10.762
- (train horn continues blaring)
- (bell clanging)

1573
01:25:10.898 --> 01:25:12.467
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know."

1574
01:25:12.603 --> 01:25:14.172
- What?
- That's what you said on TV.

1575
01:25:14.307 --> 01:25:15.774
They said I was
talking nonsense.

1576
01:25:15.910 --> 01:25:17.171
I understood every word.

1577
01:25:17.307 --> 01:25:18.979
What happened to us?

1578
01:25:19.115 --> 01:25:20.981
- (Daniel grunts)
- (gasps) Oh. my God.

1579
01:25:21.116 --> 01:25:23.077
- (tires squealing)
- (both grunting)

1580
01:25:23.212 --> 01:25:24.481
Who is it?!

1581
01:25:27.150 --> 01:25:28.312
Boyd. stop!

1582
01:25:28.447 --> 01:25:29.585
Boyd!

1583
01:25:31.924 --> 01:25:33.855
(engine revving)

1584
01:25:33.991 --> 01:25:35.690
(grunts)

1585
01:25:38.831 --> 01:25:39.859
Shit.

1586
01:25:40.969 --> 01:25:42.531
We got to jump! We got to bail!

1587
01:25:42.666 --> 01:25:44.501
I can't!
I'm standing on the brakes!

1588
01:25:48.602 --> 01:25:50.474
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!

1589
01:25:52.640 --> 01:25:53.774
No. no. no. no. no. no. no!

1590
01:25:56.216 --> 01:25:57.778
He's backing up! Get out now!

1591
01:26:08.290 --> 01:26:10.296
(both grunting)

1592
01:26:11.499 --> 01:26:13.266
- (Margaret screaming)
- All right. all right!

1593
01:26:21.810 --> 01:26:23.243
Get to the ladder!

1594
01:26:29.217 --> 01:26:31.146
MARGARET:
Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1595
01:26:31.281 --> 01:26:32.580
DANIEL:
Okay.

1596
01:26:32.716 --> 01:26:34.419
(train horn blasting
in distance)

1597
01:26:38.719 --> 01:26:40.550
(horn continues blasting)

1598
01:26:40.685 --> 01:26:42.922
(both grunting)

1599
01:26:51.999 --> 01:26:54.241
- (bullets ricocheting)
- (grunting)

1600
01:26:56.978 --> 01:26:58.672
(gasping. whimpering)

1601
01:26:58.807 --> 01:27:00.973
- (horn honking)
- (tires squealing)

1602
01:27:07.285 --> 01:27:08.347
(train horn blaring)

1603
01:27:08.482 --> 01:27:10.482
Go! Jump!

1604
01:27:10.618 --> 01:27:12.424
(metallic creaking)

1605
01:27:14.025 --> 01:27:15.823
(gasps)

1606
01:27:18.393 --> 01:27:20.894
(horn blasting)

1607
01:27:23.398 --> 01:27:25.096
You got to jump!

1608
01:27:26.071 --> 01:27:27.571
Jump! Now!

1609
01:27:32.843 --> 01:27:35.612
- (Daniel straining)
- (breathing heavily)

1610
01:27:37.578 --> 01:27:39.286
(muffled shouting)

1611
01:27:49.655 --> 01:27:52.123
(grunting)

1612
01:27:53.936 --> 01:27:56.270
(heavy. gasping breaths)

1613
01:28:02.206 --> 01:28:03.607
Oh. my God.

1614
01:28:07.412 --> 01:28:10.581
(piano strings resonating)

1615
01:28:11.747 --> 01:28:14.486
I can't breathe.
I can't breathe.

1616
01:28:15.450 --> 01:28:16.785
I can't breathe.

1617
01:28:18.218 --> 01:28:20.351
- It's okay. It's okay.
- I can't breathe.

1618
01:28:20.487 --> 01:28:22.021
- I think you're having
a panic attack.
- Oh. my God.

1619
01:28:22.156 --> 01:28:24.255
- It's okay. It's okay.
- Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1620
01:28:24.391 --> 01:28:26.133
- It's okay. I'm used to 'em.
- (stammers) My hands.

1621
01:28:26.268 --> 01:28:27.963
- We're okay.
- It's like my dad.

1622
01:28:28.099 --> 01:28:29.534
- It's like my dad. My hands.
- No. no. no. No. no. no. no.

1623
01:28:29.670 --> 01:28:31.501
It's like Parkinson's.
It's like Parkinson's.

1624
01:28:31.637 --> 01:28:32.862
It's not the same thing.
It's not that.

1625
01:28:32.998 --> 01:28:34.540
Yes. it is. It's the same.

1626
01:28:34.675 --> 01:28:36.440
No. he couldn't control it.
I can't control it.

1627
01:28:36.575 --> 01:28:38.037
- I can't control it.
- You can.

1628
01:28:38.172 --> 01:28:40.813
(sobbing): Oh. my God.
I ran away from him.

1629
01:28:40.949 --> 01:28:43.644
- I didn't want to be
around him anymore.
- No. no. no. Stop.

1630
01:28:43.779 --> 01:28:45.515
- I want this gone!
- Okay.

1631
01:28:45.651 --> 01:28:48.379
I just want it gone!
I want it gone!

1632
01:28:48.515 --> 01:28:51.115
I want it gone! I just have
no mind of my own anymore!

1633
01:28:51.251 --> 01:28:53.090
Okay. stop! Stop!
Stop talking! Stop.

1634
01:28:53.226 --> 01:28:54.359
Give me your hands.

1635
01:28:54.494 --> 01:28:55.690
- Okay. look at me.
- No. no. no.

1636
01:28:55.826 --> 01:28:57.121
- Look at me.
- I-I'm gonna see things.

1637
01:28:57.256 --> 01:28:58.862
- I'm gonna see things. Please.
- Okay.

1638
01:28:58.997 --> 01:28:59.922
Breathe through your nose.
Breathe through your nose.

1639
01:29:00.058 --> 01:29:01.361
(both taking deep breaths)

1640
01:29:01.496 --> 01:29:03.101
That's it. Okay.

1641
01:29:03.236 --> 01:29:05.167
I can't feel my hands.

1642
01:29:05.302 --> 01:29:07.097
Okay. Okay.

1643
01:29:07.233 --> 01:29:08.938
Okay. give me your hands.
Come on.

1644
01:29:09.074 --> 01:29:10.670
- Come on. Put your hands there.
- (piano strings thrumming)

1645
01:29:10.805 --> 01:29:12.670
Feel that. Okay. you feel that?

1646
01:29:12.806 --> 01:29:14.374
I'm here. I'm here.

1647
01:29:14.509 --> 01:29:15.938
We're here.

1648
01:29:16.074 --> 01:29:17.615
- We're okay.
- Okay.

1649
01:29:18.781 --> 01:29:20.182
- We're okay.
- We're okay.

1650
01:29:20.317 --> 01:29:22.418
We're okay.

1651
01:29:22.553 --> 01:29:25.256
We're okay now. You're okay.

1652
01:29:25.391 --> 01:29:27.427
(heavy breathing continues)

1653
01:29:29.623 --> 01:29:31.665
We're okay.

1654
01:29:31.800 --> 01:29:33.065
Okay.

1655
01:29:33.200 --> 01:29:35.226
(breathing calms down)

1656
01:29:37.796 --> 01:29:39.571
Thank you.

1657
01:29:42.635 --> 01:29:44.935
Kellner called in from a gas
station outside Mount Leonard.

1658
01:29:45.070 --> 01:29:46.345
I'll meet Santiago and his crew.

1659
01:29:46.480 --> 01:29:48.415
We can be there
in a couple hours.

1660
01:29:49.512 --> 01:29:51.013
(Hugo grunts)

1661
01:29:51.149 --> 01:29:53.209
H-Hugo?

1662
01:29:53.345 --> 01:29:54.746
Could everyone leave
the staging area

1663
01:29:54.881 --> 01:29:56.247
for a minute. please?

1664
01:29:56.382 --> 01:29:59.186
- Now. please! Out!
- Yeah. Okay. let's go.

1665
01:29:59.322 --> 01:30:00.856
(sighs)

1666
01:30:03.364 --> 01:30:05.394
- (door opens)
- (groans)

1667
01:30:05.530 --> 01:30:07.159
SCANLON:
Hello. Hugo.

1668
01:30:08.365 --> 01:30:10.404
♪ ♪

1669
01:30:12.799 --> 01:30:14.939
Noah. please.

1670
01:30:15.975 --> 01:30:17.868
It's terribly misguided for you
to dive with that thing.

1671
01:30:18.003 --> 01:30:19.875
It's not a magic wand.

1672
01:30:20.010 --> 01:30:21.743
And it's not a weapon.
but it has functions

1673
01:30:21.879 --> 01:30:24.747
very far beyond
your limited use of it.

1674
01:30:24.883 --> 01:30:29.388
Kellner was an experiencer.
wasn't he?

1675
01:30:29.523 --> 01:30:31.383
That's why
I couldn't dive on him.

1676
01:30:31.519 --> 01:30:33.726
Yes.

1677
01:30:33.862 --> 01:30:35.627
He was.

1678
01:30:37.422 --> 01:30:41.501
And In Vivo 17
told you to recruit him?

1679
01:30:42.765 --> 01:30:44.599
Not in any way you'd understand.

1680
01:30:44.734 --> 01:30:46.298
If this is all their plan. Hugo.

1681
01:30:46.434 --> 01:30:48.904
you can be sure it's
in their interests. not ours.

1682
01:30:49.039 --> 01:30:51.408
That's a very lonely way
to look at the world.

1683
01:30:51.543 --> 01:30:52.904
No. don't condescend to me.

1684
01:30:53.039 --> 01:30:54.481
I'm listening to you. Noah.

1685
01:30:54.616 --> 01:30:56.576
Something I've learned
quite a bit about.

1686
01:30:56.711 --> 01:30:58.146
From your friends?

1687
01:30:58.282 --> 01:30:59.883
Yes.

1688
01:31:00.019 --> 01:31:02.817
They regard empathy
as an evolutionary advantage.

1689
01:31:02.953 --> 01:31:05.459
as the foremost
evolutionary advantage.

1690
01:31:05.594 --> 01:31:09.561
in fact. the core
of animate existence.

1691
01:31:09.696 --> 01:31:11.758
Our rejection
of this understanding

1692
01:31:11.893 --> 01:31:14.097
is leading us to our extinction.

1693
01:31:15.100 --> 01:31:18.131
And is your bleeding heart
why you helped it escape?

1694
01:31:20.107 --> 01:31:21.634
Five years ago.

1695
01:31:21.770 --> 01:31:23.675
That was you. wasn't it?

1696
01:31:25.408 --> 01:31:26.678
Yes.

1697
01:31:27.945 --> 01:31:30.779
The utter insanity
of that act aside.

1698
01:31:30.914 --> 01:31:33.113
how could you lie to me
for five years

1699
01:31:33.248 --> 01:31:34.852
every time you walked
through the door?

1700
01:31:34.987 --> 01:31:37.689
Everything you said to me.
it was all diversion.

1701
01:31:39.661 --> 01:31:42.822
When precisely did you lose
your bearings?

1702
01:31:42.957 --> 01:31:45.323
Around the time you lost yours.

1703
01:31:47.762 --> 01:31:49.360
When you lost her.

1704
01:31:53.698 --> 01:31:56.340
You lost her and almost
immediately were lost to me.

1705
01:31:56.475 --> 01:31:57.704
Because you shut down.

1706
01:31:57.840 --> 01:31:59.269
Do not presume to know me.

1707
01:31:59.405 --> 01:32:00.675
When she died.
you reduced everyone

1708
01:32:00.811 --> 01:32:02.347
to need-to-know. including me.

1709
01:32:02.482 --> 01:32:03.645
Because you were very clear.

1710
01:32:03.780 --> 01:32:05.144
All you needed to know was them.

1711
01:32:05.279 --> 01:32:07.481
and they are not knowable.
not by us.

1712
01:32:07.617 --> 01:32:10.156
They will be.

1713
01:32:10.291 --> 01:32:12.348
In Vivo 17 is nonhuman

1714
01:32:12.484 --> 01:32:14.194
but nearer to God. Noah.
than you or I.

1715
01:32:14.329 --> 01:32:16.288
You don't need to fear them.

1716
01:32:17.296 --> 01:32:19.194
I fear us.

1717
01:32:19.330 --> 01:32:22.362
The entire reason WARDEX exists
is because of our knowledge.

1718
01:32:22.498 --> 01:32:26.562
certain that the human race
cannot accept what we know.

1719
01:32:26.698 --> 01:32:28.404
That truth will upend
all established order

1720
01:32:28.540 --> 01:32:29.839
across the entire world.

1721
01:32:29.974 --> 01:32:32.370
The archive Kellner stole
is a virus

1722
01:32:32.505 --> 01:32:36.714
against which
the world has zero immunity.

1723
01:32:36.849 --> 01:32:39.175
I have spent 35 years
protecting...

1724
01:32:39.310 --> 01:32:40.585
Your own wealth and power--

1725
01:32:40.720 --> 01:32:42.384
that's all
you've been protecting.

1726
01:32:42.519 --> 01:32:45.285
Noah. Noah.

1727
01:32:45.420 --> 01:32:47.559
There is an essential need
in all of us to believe

1728
01:32:47.694 --> 01:32:50.927
and an equal need
to be believed.

1729
01:32:51.062 --> 01:32:53.199
You've violated
every standard of evidence.

1730
01:32:53.335 --> 01:32:54.932
You've infantilized anyone

1731
01:32:55.068 --> 01:32:57.636
who only wanted to understand
what they've witnessed.

1732
01:32:57.771 --> 01:33:00.573
You've brutally stifled
their questions.

1733
01:33:00.709 --> 01:33:03.267
shouted them down.
ridiculed and shamed

1734
01:33:03.403 --> 01:33:05.102
and overridden them
for the crime

1735
01:33:05.237 --> 01:33:07.207
of simply being astonished.

1736
01:33:07.342 --> 01:33:10.041
We believe the believers
and then deny the world

1737
01:33:10.176 --> 01:33:11.950
the chance to believe them. too.

1738
01:33:12.085 --> 01:33:14.619
But people keep wondering.
encountering the unknown.

1739
01:33:14.755 --> 01:33:16.388
telling others
of their experiences.

1740
01:33:16.523 --> 01:33:18.786
They are starved for the truth.

1741
01:33:18.921 --> 01:33:22.387
This 79-year terror campaign

1742
01:33:22.522 --> 01:33:26.027
of obfuscation. lies
and cover-up has to end!

1743
01:33:26.162 --> 01:33:27.964
We're ready to show you
a demonstration.

1744
01:33:28.099 --> 01:33:30.468
- HUGO: Get out! Get out!
- Sorry. sir. we have...

1745
01:33:30.603 --> 01:33:32.639
Turn around and get out now!

1746
01:33:38.078 --> 01:33:40.944
Pull up the 12 who didn't
show up to work yesterday.

1747
01:33:41.079 --> 01:33:43.978
I need faces
who are with him right now.

1748
01:33:44.114 --> 01:33:46.617
- Her.
- Grace Zhao. neuro-services.

1749
01:33:46.752 --> 01:33:48.286
- Him.
- Nathan Twinning.

1750
01:33:48.421 --> 01:33:49.821
Hugo's chief aide.

1751
01:33:49.956 --> 01:33:51.418
Got a back door
into their mobile providers.

1752
01:33:51.554 --> 01:33:53.253
Hang on.

1753
01:33:56.295 --> 01:34:00.766
They shut down their phones
last night... right here.

1754
01:34:02.100 --> 01:34:03.827
I'll project their routes ahead
to overlap.

1755
01:34:03.962 --> 01:34:06.669
I can give you the AI model
within a quarter-mile radius.

1756
01:34:06.804 --> 01:34:08.840
(Scanlon breathing heavily)

1757
01:34:12.978 --> 01:34:15.248
(church bell tolling
in distance)

1758
01:34:15.383 --> 01:34:17.849
Sister Maura. Sister.

1759
01:34:20.080 --> 01:34:22.117
(indistinct whispering)

1760
01:34:26.127 --> 01:34:27.523
Jane?

1761
01:34:27.659 --> 01:34:29.088
Where are you. Jane?

1762
01:34:29.223 --> 01:34:30.862
- (quiet chatter)
- (bell dinging)

1763
01:34:31.959 --> 01:34:33.491
Does God love us?

1764
01:34:33.626 --> 01:34:36.566
I don't mean. does he love us?
I know he does.

1765
01:34:36.701 --> 01:34:40.401
Does he love only us?

1766
01:34:40.536 --> 01:34:42.741
'Cause Genesis says that
we're his supreme creation.

1767
01:34:42.877 --> 01:34:45.544
but do you think
it's possible that...

1768
01:34:45.679 --> 01:34:47.142
SISTER MAURA:
On Earth.

1769
01:34:48.446 --> 01:34:49.575
What?

1770
01:34:49.711 --> 01:34:51.213
Genesis.

1771
01:34:51.348 --> 01:34:56.019
It says we are God's
supreme creation on Earth.

1772
01:34:57.721 --> 01:34:59.385
(bell dinging)

1773
01:35:05.129 --> 01:35:07.162
Do you think
there could be others?

1774
01:35:08.829 --> 01:35:10.863
Yes.

1775
01:35:10.998 --> 01:35:12.563
I would think so.

1776
01:35:12.698 --> 01:35:16.308
Why would he make
such a vast universe.

1777
01:35:16.444 --> 01:35:20.472
yet save it only for us?

1778
01:35:21.541 --> 01:35:26.643
If you found out
we weren't alone. if...

1779
01:35:26.778 --> 01:35:30.317
if someone showed you.
proved it to you...

1780
01:35:32.153 --> 01:35:34.385
...would that frighten you?

1781
01:35:34.521 --> 01:35:37.287
SISTER MAURA:
No. Why? Should it?

1782
01:35:37.423 --> 01:35:40.593
But what if it all collapsed?

1783
01:35:40.728 --> 01:35:43.059
For you and every other person
of faith in the world.

1784
01:35:43.194 --> 01:35:44.234
Then what?

1785
01:35:44.370 --> 01:35:45.534
Oh.

1786
01:35:45.670 --> 01:35:47.864
My dear. Jane.

1787
01:35:48.000 --> 01:35:52.910
I don't think that you ever
doubted your belief in God.

1788
01:35:53.046 --> 01:35:55.980
I think you lost your faith
in people.

1789
01:36:00.551 --> 01:36:03.988
They say you're paying because
you borrowed their phone?

1790
01:36:11.258 --> 01:36:12.893
Are you near the computer?

1791
01:36:13.029 --> 01:36:14.530
SISTER MAURA:
Yes.

1792
01:36:14.666 --> 01:36:16.897
What is KCXE?

1793
01:36:17.033 --> 01:36:19.597
Just those letters-- KCXE.

1794
01:36:26.943 --> 01:36:28.873
Remember being a kid?

1795
01:36:29.008 --> 01:36:30.406
Sure.

1796
01:36:30.542 --> 01:36:32.951
Mostly stuff after I was ten.

1797
01:36:38.082 --> 01:36:42.092
Can you tell anything about me
from when I was small?

1798
01:36:46.796 --> 01:36:48.835
♪ ♪

1799
01:37:01.074 --> 01:37:03.113
It's just a fox.

1800
01:37:10.051 --> 01:37:13.090
(brakes squealing)

1801
01:37:16.631 --> 01:37:18.125
DANIEL:
No. no. no. No!

1802
01:37:18.260 --> 01:37:21.030
- Stop! Stop!
- No. Daniel!

1803
01:37:21.166 --> 01:37:22.933
- (indistinct chatter)
- (grunting)

1804
01:37:23.068 --> 01:37:24.427
- Let's go. Come with us.
- Hold on.

1805
01:37:24.562 --> 01:37:26.603
- Hold on.
- Let's go.

1806
01:37:26.739 --> 01:37:28.334
I know him. I know him.

1807
01:37:28.470 --> 01:37:29.974
We just got to check you
real quick.

1808
01:37:30.110 --> 01:37:32.478
make sure nobody's in there
with you.

1809
01:37:32.613 --> 01:37:34.177
(electronic trilling)

1810
01:37:38.751 --> 01:37:39.812
(electronic trilling)

1811
01:37:39.947 --> 01:37:41.410
Clear.

1812
01:37:41.546 --> 01:37:43.580
All right. let's load up.

1813
01:37:43.716 --> 01:37:45.318
See. the thing about
fire trucks--

1814
01:37:45.454 --> 01:37:47.821
everyone gets the hell
out of your way.

1815
01:37:47.956 --> 01:37:49.995
♪ ♪

1816
01:38:04.007 --> 01:38:05.879
(Daniel inhales deeply)

1817
01:38:08.383 --> 01:38:10.411
♪ ♪

1818
01:38:36.501 --> 01:38:38.268
I knew you'd make it.

1819
01:38:38.403 --> 01:38:39.873
I'm glad you knew.

1820
01:38:40.009 --> 01:38:41.607
Never a doubt.

1821
01:38:48.788 --> 01:38:50.451
DANIEL:
Margaret.

1822
01:38:52.185 --> 01:38:53.619
Margaret.

1823
01:38:56.596 --> 01:38:57.964
Hello. Margaret.

1824
01:39:00.129 --> 01:39:02.325
Do you know who I am?

1825
01:39:02.461 --> 01:39:03.937
Of course. You're Hugo.

1826
01:39:06.770 --> 01:39:08.304
Nathan.

1827
01:39:09.709 --> 01:39:13.236
Chloe. Malik.

1828
01:39:13.371 --> 01:39:15.905
Jordan. Letisha.

1829
01:39:17.110 --> 01:39:18.912
Grace.

1830
01:39:19.047 --> 01:39:20.651
Hi. Terri.

1831
01:39:20.787 --> 01:39:22.714
Kaitlyn. That's Everett.

1832
01:39:32.863 --> 01:39:34.891
♪ ♪

1833
01:39:50.279 --> 01:39:52.381
I think we got it mostly right.

1834
01:39:53.950 --> 01:39:55.313
Margaret.

1835
01:39:55.449 --> 01:39:57.987
Why won't you look at me?

1836
01:39:58.123 --> 01:39:59.617
Because you're-you're the guy.

1837
01:39:59.753 --> 01:40:01.852
You're the guy
who knows everything.

1838
01:40:03.528 --> 01:40:06.329
And I'm... and I'm not ready
to know everything.

1839
01:40:08.128 --> 01:40:11.561
Including. like. why-why my mom
and dad's entire goddamn house

1840
01:40:11.696 --> 01:40:13.038
is just sitting right there!

1841
01:40:13.174 --> 01:40:16.339
What is going on?
Why are you doing this?

1842
01:40:16.474 --> 01:40:18.371
That's where I grew up.
That's where I grew up.

1843
01:40:18.506 --> 01:40:21.674
This is my life.
This is my life.

1844
01:40:21.809 --> 01:40:24.007
And this matters--
what I want. who I am.

1845
01:40:24.142 --> 01:40:27.713
not who I am as you
or him or her. but as me.

1846
01:40:31.925 --> 01:40:33.820
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

1847
01:40:33.956 --> 01:40:36.161
No. No.

1848
01:40:37.755 --> 01:40:40.396
I will not be anyone's religion.

1849
01:40:48.235 --> 01:40:50.571
(sobbing)

1850
01:40:53.306 --> 01:40:55.345
♪ ♪

1851
01:41:05.692 --> 01:41:07.720
♪ ♪

1852
01:41:23.744 --> 01:41:25.870
(whimpers softly)

1853
01:41:51.066 --> 01:41:52.501
My room.

1854
01:41:56.369 --> 01:41:58.243
Oh. my room.

1855
01:42:25.236 --> 01:42:27.739
Why would you build all of this?

1856
01:42:27.875 --> 01:42:30.308
To create a passage.

1857
01:42:32.375 --> 01:42:34.343
To return you to your experience

1858
01:42:34.478 --> 01:42:37.308
in the most familiar way
possible.

1859
01:42:37.443 --> 01:42:39.680
What experience?

1860
01:42:41.915 --> 01:42:44.113
The one you shared
with Margaret.

1861
01:42:45.891 --> 01:42:47.023
I shared?

1862
01:42:47.159 --> 01:42:49.428
I am not going back there.

1863
01:42:49.564 --> 01:42:51.187
- Hugo.
- How much do you remember
about that night?

1864
01:42:51.322 --> 01:42:53.023
I don't remember.
and I don't want to remember.

1865
01:42:53.158 --> 01:42:54.726
and I don't want you
making me remember.

1866
01:42:54.861 --> 01:42:56.964
- Okay. Oh. my...
- HUGO: Wait. Wait.

1867
01:42:57.099 --> 01:42:58.866
Wait.

1868
01:42:59.002 --> 01:43:00.836
Everything that happened to you
on the 23rd of February. 1996.

1869
01:43:00.972 --> 01:43:02.472
- is blocked.
- I don't want to know
anything about it.

1870
01:43:02.607 --> 01:43:03.900
The only way for you
to know what's next

1871
01:43:04.036 --> 01:43:05.741
is to understand
what came before.

1872
01:43:05.877 --> 01:43:07.145
I don't want to talk about it.
I don't. Stop. stop. stop.

1873
01:43:07.281 --> 01:43:08.676
And then you'll know
your purpose.

1874
01:43:08.811 --> 01:43:10.005
Please don't make me.
I don't want to hear it.

1875
01:43:10.141 --> 01:43:10.981
You won't be
a passenger anymore.

1876
01:43:11.116 --> 01:43:12.713
I told you no! (gasps)

1877
01:43:17.521 --> 01:43:20.817
You have the gift
but no control.

1878
01:43:20.952 --> 01:43:22.953
No understanding
of your purpose.

1879
01:43:23.088 --> 01:43:24.688
Not a clue as to
what your situation

1880
01:43:24.823 --> 01:43:27.022
will demand of you beyond today.

1881
01:43:27.158 --> 01:43:29.531
The only way for you
to acquire it

1882
01:43:29.666 --> 01:43:33.067
is to go back
to where it all began.

1883
01:43:33.202 --> 01:43:34.867
To go home.

1884
01:43:40.976 --> 01:43:45.008
And when you do. Margaret.
you'll know everything.

1885
01:43:45.144 --> 01:43:48.353
More than what was ever
humanly possible.

1886
01:44:09.603 --> 01:44:11.807
They gifted each of you.

1887
01:44:11.943 --> 01:44:14.903
Margaret. what was dormant
in you for most of your life

1888
01:44:15.039 --> 01:44:17.745
was activated only yesterday.

1889
01:44:18.744 --> 01:44:21.318
And yours. 15 years ago.

1890
01:44:21.454 --> 01:44:23.422
They gave you fluency
in the language

1891
01:44:23.557 --> 01:44:25.889
in which the book
of the universe is written:

1892
01:44:26.024 --> 01:44:27.758
mathematics.

1893
01:44:27.893 --> 01:44:31.354
Taught it to you. imbued it
so you could understand them.

1894
01:44:32.357 --> 01:44:36.467
And they imbued you
so you could understand us.

1895
01:44:38.731 --> 01:44:41.135
It's the two of you.

1896
01:44:41.270 --> 01:44:42.702
(chuckles)

1897
01:44:42.838 --> 01:44:46.411
It's always been
just the two of you.

1898
01:44:54.946 --> 01:44:56.982
(quiet. indistinct chatter)

1899
01:45:08.661 --> 01:45:10.268
You can direct it

1900
01:45:10.404 --> 01:45:12.602
or feel where it wants
to take you.

1901
01:45:13.836 --> 01:45:15.802
It can find
what you're looking for.

1902
01:45:15.937 --> 01:45:18.805
It'll be an instrument
of your will.

1903
01:45:18.941 --> 01:45:21.314
But you must give yourself
over to it.

1904
01:45:22.614 --> 01:45:24.944
I'll find out
what's happening to me.

1905
01:45:27.447 --> 01:45:28.810
What?

1906
01:45:28.946 --> 01:45:30.481
It's gonna be okay.

1907
01:45:30.616 --> 01:45:32.116
I promise.

1908
01:45:39.295 --> 01:45:41.334
♪ ♪

1909
01:45:49.308 --> 01:45:50.870
Whatever happens. Daniel.

1910
01:45:51.005 --> 01:45:53.038
- don't you let go.
- Don't you let go.

1911
01:45:56.246 --> 01:45:57.713
Margaret.

1912
01:46:00.179 --> 01:46:02.311
Look around the room
one more time.

1913
01:46:03.814 --> 01:46:05.853
♪ ♪

1914
01:46:09.223 --> 01:46:12.693
You're a ten-year-old girl
asleep in your bed.

1915
01:46:12.829 --> 01:46:14.699
Something woke you up.
didn't it?

1916
01:46:14.835 --> 01:46:16.033
Yes.

1917
01:46:16.169 --> 01:46:17.865
So what did you do?

1918
01:46:18.862 --> 01:46:20.934
I sang my song.

1919
01:46:23.004 --> 01:46:26.038
(humming
"Someday My Prince Will Come")

1920
01:46:36.455 --> 01:46:40.024
♪ And away to his castle ♪

1921
01:46:40.159 --> 01:46:42.522
♪ We'll go ♪

1922
01:46:42.658 --> 01:46:46.360
♪ To be happy forever ♪

1923
01:46:46.495 --> 01:46:49.168
♪ I know ♪

1924
01:46:49.303 --> 01:46:53.263
♪ And the birds will sing. ♪

1925
01:46:59.210 --> 01:47:01.238
♪ ♪

1926
01:47:03.742 --> 01:47:06.116
I can see them.

1927
01:47:06.251 --> 01:47:08.252
Right over there.

1928
01:47:08.388 --> 01:47:10.214
They're coming into the room.

1929
01:47:12.751 --> 01:47:14.790
♪ ♪

1930
01:47:16.692 --> 01:47:19.729
(gruff. heavy breathing nearby)

1931
01:47:36.413 --> 01:47:37.747
(chitters softly)

1932
01:48:01.404 --> 01:48:03.432
♪ ♪

1933
01:48:06.404 --> 01:48:08.277
DANIEL:
No. no. no. don't go with them.

1934
01:48:08.413 --> 01:48:09.779
They're not animals.

1935
01:48:09.914 --> 01:48:11.841
Don't go with them.
They're not animals.

1936
01:48:11.977 --> 01:48:13.485
They're not animals!

1937
01:48:13.621 --> 01:48:15.213
- It's okay. It's okay.
- (panting) They're not.

1938
01:48:15.348 --> 01:48:19.184
They-they present as animals
to calm us.

1939
01:48:24.430 --> 01:48:27.060
When I walked through the glass.

1940
01:48:27.195 --> 01:48:31.130
it was like
this curtain of warm water.

1941
01:48:33.931 --> 01:48:36.338
And the snow...

1942
01:48:36.474 --> 01:48:39.710
was so warm on my feet.

1943
01:48:41.511 --> 01:48:44.345
(long. slow gasp)

1944
01:48:44.480 --> 01:48:46.442
The house.

1945
01:48:52.688 --> 01:48:55.286
"Hansel and Gretel."

1946
01:49:11.972 --> 01:49:14.008
(soft electrical warbling)

1947
01:49:20.384 --> 01:49:22.412
♪ ♪

1948
01:49:25.359 --> 01:49:27.384
(soft electrical warbling)

1949
01:49:30.658 --> 01:49:32.697
(soft whooshing)

1950
01:49:40.539 --> 01:49:42.067
(gruff. heavy breathing nearby)

1951
01:49:42.202 --> 01:49:44.775
(young Margaret
breathing heavily)

1952
01:49:57.322 --> 01:50:00.054
(chittering)

1953
01:50:10.766 --> 01:50:13.463
(rapid. gasping breaths)

1954
01:50:25.118 --> 01:50:26.784
Shh.

1955
01:50:32.622 --> 01:50:34.858
Hold my hand.

1956
01:50:43.804 --> 01:50:46.100
(young Daniel's breathing
slowing down)

1957
01:50:53.576 --> 01:50:55.604
♪ ♪

1958
01:50:58.484 --> 01:51:00.510
(trembling breaths)

1959
01:51:03.053 --> 01:51:05.152
- (soft electrical whooshing)
- (gasps)

1960
01:51:11.960 --> 01:51:13.996
(soft electrical crackling)

1961
01:51:27.140 --> 01:51:30.177
(soft whooshing. crackling)

1962
01:51:31.980 --> 01:51:34.016
- (sharp whoosh)
- (gasps)

1963
01:51:43.263 --> 01:51:45.291
♪ ♪

1964
01:51:48.125 --> 01:51:50.164
(soft whirring)

1965
01:51:53.702 --> 01:51:55.565
(soft whooshing)

1966
01:52:06.013 --> 01:52:08.050
(breathing heavily)

1967
01:52:11.620 --> 01:52:13.055
Whoa.

1968
01:52:15.019 --> 01:52:16.729
Whoa.

1969
01:52:33.511 --> 01:52:35.539
♪ ♪

1970
01:52:54.433 --> 01:52:56.230
Hello. Hugo.

1971
01:52:59.598 --> 01:53:01.807
It's so nice
to finally know you.

1972
01:53:02.838 --> 01:53:04.704
(tires squealing)

1973
01:53:04.839 --> 01:53:06.878
♪ ♪

1974
01:53:15.951 --> 01:53:17.988
(indistinct chatter)

1975
01:53:19.217 --> 01:53:20.820
They found us.

1976
01:53:20.956 --> 01:53:23.157
(labored breathing)

1977
01:53:23.293 --> 01:53:24.792
HUGO:
<i>Are they out front or out back?</i>

1978
01:53:24.928 --> 01:53:26.359
Most likely on all sides.

1979
01:53:26.494 --> 01:53:29.660
Okay. give me the. uh...
the-the-the thingy.

1980
01:53:29.795 --> 01:53:33.333
Thermal imaging showed
43 heat signatures inside here.

1981
01:53:33.469 --> 01:53:35.171
This whole area's
an industrial decay zone.

1982
01:53:35.307 --> 01:53:37.700
No other structure has
more than five people in it.

1983
01:53:39.338 --> 01:53:41.671
(heavy. labored breathing)

1984
01:53:45.311 --> 01:53:46.945
- (groans)
- Hey.

1985
01:53:47.081 --> 01:53:49.448
(grunts) Get on with it.

1986
01:53:54.218 --> 01:53:56.257
(whirring)

1987
01:54:05.838 --> 01:54:07.763
(electronic trilling. beeping)

1988
01:54:23.181 --> 01:54:25.220
♪ ♪

1989
01:54:33.800 --> 01:54:34.993
(hushed):
No one move.

1990
01:54:35.129 --> 01:54:37.369
No one make a sound.

1991
01:54:37.504 --> 01:54:38.937
They can't see us.

1992
01:54:42.476 --> 01:54:44.206
Give it to me.

1993
01:54:49.714 --> 01:54:51.477
This is not right.

1994
01:54:54.516 --> 01:54:58.187
They can't see us.
but they can see this.

1995
01:54:59.153 --> 01:55:01.851
We need to move now.

1996
01:55:01.986 --> 01:55:04.853
This is not gonna last long.
We got to go right now.

1997
01:55:15.205 --> 01:55:16.608
(hushed):
Look. They can't see me.

1998
01:55:16.743 --> 01:55:18.068
They can't see us. Let's go.

1999
01:55:18.204 --> 01:55:19.470
Quiet. quiet.

2000
01:55:19.605 --> 01:55:20.878
Through the back doors.
Any back door.

2001
01:55:21.014 --> 01:55:22.879
Go quiet. Go quiet.
Down the alley.

2002
01:55:23.014 --> 01:55:25.076
- Let's go. Let's go.
- Quiet.

2003
01:55:25.212 --> 01:55:27.980
Everybody. stop moving.

2004
01:55:28.115 --> 01:55:30.153
(rapid footsteps)

2005
01:55:36.123 --> 01:55:38.128
There. Look there.

2006
01:55:40.524 --> 01:55:42.164
Oh. God. I'm losing it.

2007
01:55:42.299 --> 01:55:43.968
I'm losing it.
You need to go faster.

2008
01:55:44.104 --> 01:55:45.770
- Get to the fire truck.
- I can't hold on.

2009
01:55:45.905 --> 01:55:47.065
- I can't hold...
- We got to go.

2010
01:55:47.200 --> 01:55:48.798
Stay on the light.

2011
01:55:51.911 --> 01:55:53.110
MARGARET:
I can't hold on.

2012
01:55:54.212 --> 01:55:56.443
- (groaning)
- (glass shattering)

2013
01:55:59.017 --> 01:56:00.110
- (loud thud)
- (groans)

2014
01:56:00.245 --> 01:56:01.411
(Margaret gasps)

2015
01:56:01.547 --> 01:56:03.280
- (creaking)
- (grunts)

2016
01:56:03.415 --> 01:56:04.885
DANIEL:
Let's go.

2017
01:56:05.020 --> 01:56:06.992
(device thrumming)

2018
01:56:08.094 --> 01:56:10.061
There. There.
Stay on the light.

2019
01:56:13.364 --> 01:56:15.627
- Stay on the light.
- The light! The light!

2020
01:56:17.966 --> 01:56:20.797
(groaning)

2021
01:56:26.271 --> 01:56:28.673
(groaning)

2022
01:56:33.520 --> 01:56:35.482
(engine starts)

2023
01:56:37.755 --> 01:56:39.490
(siren blaring)

2024
01:56:39.625 --> 01:56:41.653
(urgent chatter)

